1
00:00:02,336 --> 00:00:04,469
[♪♪]

2
00:00:04,538 --> 00:00:07,272
[ANNOUNCER]:<i> WATCH HIM
JUST THREAD THE NEEDLE,</i>

3
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:08,407
<i>A LITTLE WRIST SHOT...</i>

4
00:00:08,542 --> 00:00:10,009
<i>AND THERE, THAT SAYS IT ALL.</i>

5
00:00:10,144 --> 00:00:13,278
<i>[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]</i>

6
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:14,613
<i>THERE'S HOWE! HE SCORES!</i>

7
00:00:14,615 --> 00:00:18,283
<i>[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]</i>

8
00:00:18,319 --> 00:00:22,421
<i>IT'S A GORDIE HOWE HAT TRICK--
A GOAL, AN ASSIST, AND A FIGHT!</i>

9
00:00:25,292 --> 00:00:27,092
<i>[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]</i>

10
00:00:27,128 --> 00:00:30,428
<i>THE HEART AND SOUL
OF THE DETROIT FRANCHISE,</i>

11
00:00:30,464 --> 00:00:35,233
<i>WEARING THE RED WING NUMBER 9
FOR A RECORD 25 YEARS.</i>

12
00:00:35,269 --> 00:00:37,302
<i>[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]</i>

13
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:39,637
<i>HOWE IS ON THE ICE.
THAT'S THE ROAR FROM THE CROWD.</i>

14
00:00:39,673 --> 00:00:42,508
<i>HERE'S HOWE--
SHOOTS, SCORES!</i>

15
00:00:46,047 --> 00:00:49,214
<i>NUMBER 9
IS UNSTOPPABLE OUT THERE.</i>

16
00:00:50,584 --> 00:00:52,183
<i>THERE'S HOWE--
HE SCORES!</i>

17
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:54,452
<i>THE DETROIT RED WINGS
HAVE WON THE STANLEY CUP,</i>

18
00:00:54,488 --> 00:00:57,322
<i>AND IN 1952,
THEY LEFT NO DOUBT</i>

19
00:00:57,391 --> 00:00:59,591
<i>AS TO
THEIR COMPLETE SUPERIORITY.</i>

20
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:03,394
<i>HE MADE 22 CONSECUTIVE
ALL-STAR GAME APPEARANCES</i>

21
00:01:03,431 --> 00:01:06,865
<i>AND RETIRES AS THE NHL'S
ALL-TIME LEADING SCORER,</i>

22
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:12,237
<i>WITH AN ASTOUNDING TOTAL
OF 786 GOALS.</i>

23
00:01:14,475 --> 00:01:16,542
[WILD CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

24
00:01:22,483 --> 00:01:24,049
THANK YOU.

25
00:01:27,688 --> 00:01:30,689
PARDON THE TEAR.

26
00:01:30,691 --> 00:01:33,625
[APPLAUSE DIES DOWN]

27
00:01:33,694 --> 00:01:37,162
I'D LIKE TO THANK MY CHILDREN
FOR STANDING BY ME TONIGHT.

28
00:01:37,297 --> 00:01:39,231
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

29
00:01:39,233 --> 00:01:40,365
AND MOST OF ALL,

30
00:01:40,501 --> 00:01:43,568
I'D LIKE TO THANK
MY DEAR WIFE, COLLEEN...

31
00:01:43,604 --> 00:01:45,103
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

32
00:01:45,106 --> 00:01:48,373
...THE BEST TEAM MATE
I EVER HAD.

33
00:01:48,409 --> 00:01:51,009
[CROWD ROARING AND CHEERING]

34
00:01:56,717 --> 00:01:59,985
I'VE BEEN A PROUD RED WING
FOR 25 YEARS...

35
00:02:03,057 --> 00:02:05,123
AND I HOPE TO BE ONE
FOR 25 MORE.

36
00:02:05,126 --> 00:02:07,059
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

37
00:02:07,194 --> 00:02:10,195
I WANT TO THANK MR. NORRIS

38
00:02:10,197 --> 00:02:11,730
FOR WELCOMING ME INTO
DETROIT'S FRONT OFFICE.

39
00:02:14,568 --> 00:02:17,002
WELL, BRUCE, I GUESS THIS IS IT.

40
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,108
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

41
00:02:25,779 --> 00:02:28,614
THANK YOU, MR. HOCKEY!

42
00:02:28,616 --> 00:02:32,684
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING
YOU'VE DONE FOR OUR RED WINGS.

43
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:34,786
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

44
00:02:40,194 --> 00:02:42,361
NOW, BRUCE, YOU MAKE SURE
TO LOOK AFTER THAT JERSEY.

45
00:02:42,363 --> 00:02:44,296
DON'T LET IT GET WRINKLED.

46
00:02:44,431 --> 00:02:46,631
WHEN MY THREE SONS COME PLAY
FOR THE DETROIT RED WINGS,

47
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:49,100
ONE OF 'EM'S GONNA WEAR IT.

48
00:02:49,136 --> 00:02:51,570
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

49
00:03:09,056 --> 00:03:12,691
[CROWD CHANTING]
GORDIE! GORDIE! GORDIE!

50
00:03:18,499 --> 00:03:21,433
[CROWD SCREAMING AND CHEERING]

51
00:04:05,179 --> 00:04:08,313
YOU MISS IT ALREADY?

52
00:04:08,382 --> 00:04:10,649
DOES IT GET
ANY EASIER TO MISS?

53
00:04:10,784 --> 00:04:12,250
YOU HUNG ON
A DAMN SIGHT LONGER

54
00:04:12,286 --> 00:04:14,186
THAN THE REST
OF US, GORDIE.

55
00:04:14,188 --> 00:04:15,387
A FEW MORE YEARS,

56
00:04:15,456 --> 00:04:17,255
YOU MIGHT'VE BEEN
PLAYING WITH YOUR BOYS.

57
00:04:17,324 --> 00:04:21,326
YEAH, THAT WOULD'VE
BEEN SOMETHING, WOULDN'T IT?

58
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:27,132
[CAR HORN HONKS A GREETING]

59
00:04:27,134 --> 00:04:28,199
SWEETIE, YOU KNOW WHY--

60
00:04:28,269 --> 00:04:30,335
OH! OKAY, HE'S HERE.

61
00:04:30,337 --> 00:04:31,336
YOU GOT YOUR TRAIN TICKETS?

62
00:04:31,372 --> 00:04:32,403
HERE YOU GO, MARTY.
YEAH.

63
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:33,538
OKAY, BYE.

64
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:35,206
ALL RIGHT,
LOVE YOU, MOM. SEE YOU.

65
00:04:35,242 --> 00:04:36,074
LOVE YOU. HAVE A GOOD DAY.
CALL ME WHEN YOU GET THERE.

66
00:04:36,143 --> 00:04:36,941
BYE. LOVE YOU.

67
00:04:36,977 --> 00:04:37,809
LOVE YOU, TOO.

68
00:04:37,811 --> 00:04:38,676
WE'LL CATCH YOU LATER.

69
00:04:38,712 --> 00:04:39,678
BYE.

70
00:04:39,747 --> 00:04:41,813
ALL RIGHT,
WHERE ARE WE?

71
00:04:41,882 --> 00:04:44,283
HEY, YOU'RE NOT
LEAVING ALREADY?

72
00:04:44,418 --> 00:04:46,217
YEAH, THE MARLIES
CALLED A TEAM MEETING.

73
00:04:46,287 --> 00:04:47,752
WE GOTTA GET BACK
TO TORONTO.

74
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:49,421
LET ME DRIVE YOU
TO THE STATION.

75
00:04:49,423 --> 00:04:50,689
BARRY'S TAKING US.

76
00:04:50,824 --> 00:04:51,823
SEE YOU, DAD.

77
00:04:51,825 --> 00:04:53,225
[STAMMERING]

78
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:54,893
WE'LL BE UP TO SEE YOU
IN THE MEMORIAL CUP.

79
00:04:54,895 --> 00:04:56,328
[DOOR SWINGS SHUT]

80
00:04:58,699 --> 00:04:59,698
ALL RIGHT, MURRAY,

81
00:04:59,700 --> 00:05:00,832
I'VE GOT THE ROBINSONS

82
00:05:00,868 --> 00:05:02,501
PICKING YOU UP
FOR HOCKEY TONIGHT,

83
00:05:02,503 --> 00:05:04,168
AND, OH, HON', CAN YOU
TAKE CATHY TO CHEERLEADING?

84
00:05:04,204 --> 00:05:05,636
I NEED TO MEET WITH

85
00:05:05,673 --> 00:05:08,473
THE JUNIOR
RED WINGS SPONSOR. YUP.

86
00:05:10,244 --> 00:05:13,245
I THINK I CAN
SQUEEZE IT INTO MY DAY.

87
00:05:21,955 --> 00:05:23,689
[INTERCOM BEEPS]

88
00:05:26,927 --> 00:05:29,528
[INTERCOM BEEPING]

89
00:05:32,866 --> 00:05:34,199
[THUMPING BUTTON]

90
00:05:34,334 --> 00:05:36,267
YES?

91
00:05:36,337 --> 00:05:37,335
[CLICKS OTHER BUTTON]

92
00:05:37,338 --> 00:05:38,603
YES?

93
00:05:38,739 --> 00:05:40,405
<i>[WOMAN, OVER INTERCOM]:
EXCUSE ME, MR. HOWE.</i>

94
00:05:40,407 --> 00:05:42,407
<i>MR. KOFFMAN IN MARKETING
HAS A COUSIN DOWN FROM FLINT</i>

95
00:05:42,476 --> 00:05:44,743
<i>WHO'D LIKE A PHOTO WITH YOU.</i>

96
00:05:44,878 --> 00:05:45,877
ALL RIGHT.

97
00:05:45,879 --> 00:05:47,412
<i>THANK YOU, SIR.</i>

98
00:05:56,223 --> 00:05:57,955
THANKS FOR THIS,
MR. HOWE.

99
00:05:57,991 --> 00:05:58,823
COME ON IN HERE, BOYS.

100
00:05:58,892 --> 00:06:00,825
COME ON.

101
00:06:00,894 --> 00:06:03,294
THERE WE GO, BIG SMILE!

102
00:06:03,330 --> 00:06:04,463
THERE WE GO.

103
00:06:07,568 --> 00:06:08,433
ALL RIGHT,
LET ME GIVE THE LITTLE ONE

104
00:06:08,435 --> 00:06:09,768
THE HOWE HAMMER.

105
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:10,902
OH!

106
00:06:10,938 --> 00:06:12,604
[FLASHBULB POPS]

107
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:37,529
[TEAM AT PRACTICE,
SHOUTING, STICKS SLAPPING]

108
00:06:49,610 --> 00:06:51,876
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

109
00:06:51,912 --> 00:06:53,512
WATCH IT!

110
00:07:01,288 --> 00:07:02,286
HEY THERE, ELBOWS.

111
00:07:02,322 --> 00:07:03,621
HEY!

112
00:07:03,657 --> 00:07:04,823
HOW COME I DON'T SEE YOU
AROUND HERE MORE OFTEN?

113
00:07:05,892 --> 00:07:07,959
AH, IT'S NOT REALLY
PART OF THE JOB.

114
00:07:08,028 --> 00:07:09,760
WHAT THE HELL
IS THE JOB, GORDIE?

115
00:07:09,797 --> 00:07:11,362
WELL, HAVEN'T YOU HEARD?

116
00:07:11,398 --> 00:07:12,898
I'VE GONE INTO
THE MUSHROOM BUSINESS.

117
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:15,433
YOU KNOW, THEY KEEP ME
IN A DARK ROOM,

118
00:07:15,436 --> 00:07:16,968
AND EVERY NOW AND AGAIN,
THEY OPEN THE DOOR

119
00:07:17,004 --> 00:07:18,436
AND THEY THROW SOME HORSE MANURE
ON TOP OF ME.

120
00:07:18,472 --> 00:07:20,238
[LAUGHS]

121
00:07:20,307 --> 00:07:21,439
HEY,

122
00:07:21,508 --> 00:07:22,774
YOU HEAR HOW WELL

123
00:07:22,843 --> 00:07:24,576
OUR OLD PAL BILL DINEEN'S
DOING DOWN IN HOUSTON

124
00:07:24,711 --> 00:07:25,911
WITH THAT NEW WHA LEAGUE?

125
00:07:27,014 --> 00:07:28,780
WE WHISPER ABOUT THE WHA
AROUND HERE, GORDIE.

126
00:07:28,782 --> 00:07:30,581
HMM?

127
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:32,317
THERE'S A SLAVE REVOLT
GOING ON,

128
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:35,053
AND THE MASTERS HAVE EARS.

129
00:07:38,725 --> 00:07:39,925
AH...

130
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:43,261
WELL, I ALWAYS KNEW FOXY
WOULD MAKE A GOOD COACH.

131
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:44,395
HELL, HE'S EVEN GOT
OLD DOUG HARVEY

132
00:07:44,465 --> 00:07:46,063
BACK ON THE WAGON AND WORKING.

133
00:07:46,099 --> 00:07:48,800
IT'S NICE TO SEE YOU.

134
00:07:48,869 --> 00:07:50,101
ALL RIGHT.

135
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:05,350
HEY, GORDIE!

136
00:08:05,419 --> 00:08:07,018
GREAT GAME TONIGHT!

137
00:08:07,153 --> 00:08:09,754
CONGRATULATIONS,
BIG FELLA.

138
00:08:09,823 --> 00:08:11,890
YOUR BOYS ARE
MEMORIAL CUP CHAMPIONS.

139
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,291
NOT ONLY THAT,

140
00:08:13,426 --> 00:08:14,626
THEY'RE GONNA BE STUDS
IN THE NHL, TOO.

141
00:08:14,761 --> 00:08:15,693
AW, THANK YOU.

142
00:08:15,729 --> 00:08:16,961
WE APPRECIATE
THAT, HAROLD.

143
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:18,496
COUPLE MORE YEARS
WITH THE MARLIES,

144
00:08:18,532 --> 00:08:20,031
I'LL HAVE 'EM READY
FOR THE SCOUTS.

145
00:08:20,033 --> 00:08:21,499
THEY CAN'T MISS.

146
00:08:21,568 --> 00:08:23,501
WHAT ABOUT THE SCOUTS
THAT WERE THERE TONIGHT?

147
00:08:23,504 --> 00:08:25,303
THEY WERE LOOKING AT
THE OLDER PROSPECTS,

148
00:08:25,438 --> 00:08:27,038
NOT YOUR YOUNGSTERS.

149
00:08:27,074 --> 00:08:28,506
HEY, GORDIE! COLLEEN.

150
00:08:28,542 --> 00:08:29,441
FOXY!

151
00:08:29,576 --> 00:08:30,508
HEY!

152
00:08:30,544 --> 00:08:31,576
HOW YOU DOING, HARV?

153
00:08:31,612 --> 00:08:32,911
GORDIE. COLLEEN.

154
00:08:33,046 --> 00:08:34,779
I OUGHTA HAVE
YOU DANG HORSE THIEVES

155
00:08:34,915 --> 00:08:36,380
RUN OUT OF TOWN.

156
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:37,448
EASY THERE, HAROLD.

157
00:08:37,484 --> 00:08:38,850
YOU DON'T WANT TO
HAVE A STROKE.

158
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:40,585
LISTEN, YOU TWIT.

159
00:08:40,654 --> 00:08:42,987
WHEN THIS WHA FRAUD FOLDS,

160
00:08:43,056 --> 00:08:46,525
YOU'LL BE COMING TO ME
BEGGING FOR A JOB.

161
00:08:48,996 --> 00:08:50,395
WOW, LOOKS LIKE
THE LIVESTOCK OWNERS

162
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:51,930
ARE HAVING A RANGE WAR.

163
00:08:51,999 --> 00:08:54,398
YOU KNOW THE OLD MAN
WOULD LIKE TO SEE YOU STRUNG UP

164
00:08:54,434 --> 00:08:56,734
FOR ALL THE LEAFS
JUMPING TO THE WHA.

165
00:08:56,803 --> 00:08:57,802
MORE TO COME, TOO--

166
00:08:57,804 --> 00:08:59,137
[CHILD NEARBY]: MR. HOWE!

167
00:08:59,139 --> 00:09:01,406
AH, EXCUSE ME, FELLAS.

168
00:09:01,475 --> 00:09:03,608
YEAH, YEAH.

169
00:09:03,743 --> 00:09:06,077
COLLEEN, MARK AND MARTY
PLAYED TERRIFIC TONIGHT.

170
00:09:06,079 --> 00:09:07,679
THEY BOTH SHOULD'VE WON MVP.

171
00:09:07,748 --> 00:09:08,880
AH, THANKS, FOXY.

172
00:09:08,949 --> 00:09:10,481
DOESN'T IT SEEM CRAZY

173
00:09:10,551 --> 00:09:12,417
THAT THEY'RE STUCK IN JUNIOR
FOR TWO MORE YEARS?

174
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:14,085
GORDIE TURNED PRO AT 16.

175
00:09:14,154 --> 00:09:16,153
MY BOYS CAN'T EVEN BE DRAFTED
UNTIL THEY'RE 20.

176
00:09:16,189 --> 00:09:18,823
IT'S A DIFFERENT
TIME, COLLEEN.

177
00:09:18,859 --> 00:09:20,358
WHY?

178
00:09:20,427 --> 00:09:22,627
THEY CAN VOTE, THEY CAN DRINK,
THEY CAN SMOKE,

179
00:09:22,629 --> 00:09:23,962
ABOUT THE ONLY THING
THEY CAN'T DO

180
00:09:23,964 --> 00:09:26,097
IS EARN A LIVING
PLAYING HOCKEY.

181
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:28,165
LET ME ASK YOU SOMETHING, FOXY,

182
00:09:28,201 --> 00:09:31,436
DOES YOUR WHA LEAGUE
HAVE THE SAME AGE RESTRICTIONS

183
00:09:31,505 --> 00:09:32,938
AS THE NHL?

184
00:09:34,107 --> 00:09:38,443
WELL, TO BE HONEST,
I DON'T KNOW.

185
00:09:39,513 --> 00:09:41,680
WELL, MAYBE
YOU SHOULD FIND OUT.

186
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:45,951
GOOD NIGHT, GENTLEMEN.

187
00:09:50,724 --> 00:09:53,858
DID WE JUST GET PROPOSITIONED
BY A HOCKEY MOM?

188
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:56,561
I BELIEVE
WE DID, HARV.

189
00:09:58,098 --> 00:10:00,098
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

190
00:10:02,869 --> 00:10:03,735
HELLO?

191
00:10:03,804 --> 00:10:06,004
YES, UH, ONE MOMENT.

192
00:10:06,073 --> 00:10:07,005
GORDIE?

193
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:08,472
MM-HMM?

194
00:10:08,508 --> 00:10:10,942
BILL DINEEN'S
ON THE PHONE.

195
00:10:11,011 --> 00:10:13,144
[QUIETLY] I THINK
YOU SHOULD TAKE IT.

196
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,946
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

197
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:16,014
THERE HE IS!

198
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:16,948
BOBBY!

199
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:18,683
HEY, HARV!

200
00:10:18,685 --> 00:10:20,619
[CROWD CLAMORING]

201
00:10:21,622 --> 00:10:23,755
HEY, YOU SUITING UP FOR
THE AEROS THIS SEASON, HUH?

202
00:10:23,824 --> 00:10:24,756
ROOKIE OF THE YEAR?

203
00:10:24,891 --> 00:10:28,492
IS THAT REAL RACCOON,
MRS. HULL?

204
00:10:28,528 --> 00:10:30,028
<i>[GORDIE, OVER TELEPHONE]:
FOXY! HOW YOU DOING?</i>

205
00:10:30,097 --> 00:10:31,562
GOOD, GORDIE. GOOD.

206
00:10:31,598 --> 00:10:33,565
I'M WITH HARV IN TORONTO
AT THE WHA DRAFT,

207
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:34,633
AND I JUST WANTED
TO LET YOU KNOW

208
00:10:34,768 --> 00:10:35,833
THAT WE'RE GONNA TAKE MARK

209
00:10:35,869 --> 00:10:38,036
<i>WITH OUR FIRST PICK.</i>

210
00:10:38,105 --> 00:10:39,504
YOU'RE WHAT?

211
00:10:39,506 --> 00:10:40,905
<i>OUR LAWYERS SAY IT'S LEGAL,</i>

212
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:42,107
<i>AND WE THINK THAT HE CAN PLAY
IN HOUSTON THIS YEAR.</i>

213
00:10:42,242 --> 00:10:43,842
I JUST WANTED TO GIVE YOU
THE HEADS-UP,

214
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:48,580
BECAUSE ONCE WE CHOOSE HIM,
ALL HECK'S GONNA BREAK LOOSE.

215
00:10:48,582 --> 00:10:49,914
THANK-THANK YOU, BILL.

216
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:51,115
ALL RIGHT.

217
00:10:51,184 --> 00:10:52,283
TAKE CARE, GORD.

218
00:11:08,602 --> 00:11:10,735
WHAT DID HE SAY?

219
00:11:10,737 --> 00:11:15,606
WELL, FOXY'S GONNA TAKE MARK
WITH THEIR FIRST DRAFT PICK.

220
00:11:15,642 --> 00:11:19,811
HE THINKS HE'S READY
TO TURN PRO RIGHT NOW.

221
00:11:22,049 --> 00:11:22,947
[CHUCKLES]

222
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:26,084
FROM THE TORONTO MARLIES,

223
00:11:26,086 --> 00:11:28,152
THE HOUSTON AEROS
SELECT MARK HOWE.

224
00:11:28,188 --> 00:11:30,221
[MURMURS OF SHOCK
RIPPLE THROUGH CROWD]

225
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:35,093
[BUZZ OF WHISPERED
CONVERSATIONS]

226
00:11:36,029 --> 00:11:37,695
FOXY WOULDN'T PICK YOU

227
00:11:37,764 --> 00:11:41,032
IF HE WASN'T SURE
YOU COULD PLAY AGAINST MEN.

228
00:11:42,302 --> 00:11:44,636
ALL RIGHT.

229
00:11:44,638 --> 00:11:46,504
YEAH, YOU AND MARTY
COME HOME THIS WEEKEND,

230
00:11:46,573 --> 00:11:48,173
AND WE'LL
TALK IT THROUGH.

231
00:11:48,308 --> 00:11:50,742
OKAY. BYE.

232
00:11:53,647 --> 00:11:55,780
SO, WHAT DID HE SAY?
IS HE EXCITED?

233
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:57,115
[SIGHING] UH...

234
00:11:57,250 --> 00:11:59,250
I'M NOT SURE HE COULD
TAKE IN THE HONOR.

235
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:01,119
I THINK HE'S, UH,

236
00:12:01,254 --> 00:12:03,121
HUNG OVER.

237
00:12:03,256 --> 00:12:03,988
I'M SORRY?

238
00:12:04,057 --> 00:12:07,859
HE ASKED ABOUT MARTY.

239
00:12:12,365 --> 00:12:15,667
THAT'S THE ONLY THING
HE ASKED.

240
00:12:15,802 --> 00:12:19,204
IF ANYONE'S GONNA TAKE
HIS OLDER BROTHER.

241
00:12:19,206 --> 00:12:21,672
[CHUCKLES FONDLY]

242
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:24,676
AW, HE'S
SUCH A GOOD KID.

243
00:12:31,017 --> 00:12:32,016
COULD YOU IMAGINE

244
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:34,886
IF THEY DID
TAKE MARTY, THOUGH?

245
00:12:35,021 --> 00:12:39,724
TWO HOWE BOYS
STARTING OUT TOGETHER?

246
00:12:41,862 --> 00:12:43,628
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT THINKING
ABOUT THE THIRD HOWE

247
00:12:43,697 --> 00:12:45,697
IN THAT PAINTING.

248
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:48,933
THAT WAS A FOOLISH
OLD DREAM.

249
00:12:54,708 --> 00:12:56,373
[ROOM ABUZZ WITH NEGOTIATIONS]

250
00:12:56,409 --> 00:12:58,009
<i>FOURTH PICK
TO THE HOUSTON AEROS.</i>

251
00:13:03,850 --> 00:13:05,182
WHAT ABOUT THE SWEDE?

252
00:13:05,218 --> 00:13:06,985
INGE HAMMARSTROM--

253
00:13:06,987 --> 00:13:09,721
I CAN'T PRONOUNCE
HIS NAME EITHER.

254
00:13:09,856 --> 00:13:11,722
WHAT ABOUT MARTY HOWE?

255
00:13:11,758 --> 00:13:14,058
ANOTHER UNDERAGE PICK?

256
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:16,060
ANOTHER HOWE?

257
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:22,267
FROM THE TORONTO MARLIES,

258
00:13:22,402 --> 00:13:24,335
HOUSTON SELECTS MARTY HOWE.

259
00:13:24,337 --> 00:13:28,072
[ROOM ERUPTS WITH CHUCKLES]

260
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,675
HEY, FOXY, WHO'S NEXT, COLLEEN?

261
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:33,945
[LAUGHTER]

262
00:13:35,215 --> 00:13:36,347
IF THOSE HOWE SIGNINGS
GO THROUGH,

263
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:37,949
EVERY HOT-SHOT JUNIOR

264
00:13:37,951 --> 00:13:40,618
IS GOING TO BE SHAKING ME DOWN
FOR SIX FIGURES!

265
00:13:40,687 --> 00:13:42,152
WE ALREADY LOST
TO THE WHA

266
00:13:42,189 --> 00:13:44,288
OVER HULL
AND THE RESERVE CLAUSE.

267
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:47,892
WE'LL LOSE THIS ONE, TOO,
IF WE TAKE IT TO THE COURTS.

268
00:13:47,928 --> 00:13:50,361
DANG PLAYER SALARIES ARE
GOING THROUGH THE ROOF.

269
00:13:50,363 --> 00:13:53,898
THESE CON ARTISTS
HAVE STOLEN HALF MY TEAM!

270
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:56,701
NOW I GOTTA WATCH 'EM
ROB THE CRADLE TOO?

271
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:59,103
I'LL ASK PRESIDENT CAMPBELL
TO CALL HOWE PERSONALLY.

272
00:13:59,139 --> 00:14:01,305
YOU KNOW, GORDIE'S ALWAYS
BEEN VERY RESPECTFUL

273
00:14:01,374 --> 00:14:03,107
WHEN IT COMES TO
THE GOOD OF THE GAME.

274
00:14:03,243 --> 00:14:05,276
YEAH, YOU DO THAT.

275
00:14:09,115 --> 00:14:11,382
YOU GOTTA LEAN ON
THE BIG FELLA.

276
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,318
IF THEY SIGN THOSE JUNIORS,

277
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:15,353
THE BUZZARDS'LL BE KICKING US
WHERE IT COUNTS.

278
00:14:21,828 --> 00:14:23,194
I TALKED WITH THE GM,

279
00:14:23,263 --> 00:14:24,461
AND WE'RE GONNA BRING YOU
MORE INTO HOCKEY OPERATIONS

280
00:14:24,497 --> 00:14:26,797
NOW, GORDIE.

281
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:29,200
WELL, THAT'S ALL
I EVER WANTED, BRUCE.

282
00:14:29,202 --> 00:14:30,134
GOOD.

283
00:14:30,136 --> 00:14:31,202
GOOD, THAT'S SETTLED.

284
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:32,337
NOW, I UNDERSTAND
CLARENCE CAMPBELL CALLED YOU

285
00:14:32,472 --> 00:14:36,874
ABOUT YOUR SONS?

286
00:14:36,910 --> 00:14:37,875
HE SET YOU STRAIGHT

287
00:14:37,944 --> 00:14:40,011
ABOUT THEM SIGNING
WITH THIS PHONY LEAGUE

288
00:14:40,013 --> 00:14:41,379
THAT'S ROBBING US?

289
00:14:43,016 --> 00:14:45,350
WELL, BRUCE...

290
00:14:45,352 --> 00:14:46,751
NOW, WHAT KIND OF FATHER
WOULD I BE

291
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,220
IF I DENIED MY BOYS
THE OPPORTUNITY

292
00:14:49,222 --> 00:14:51,956
TO MAKE A LIVING
DOING WHAT THEY LOVE?

293
00:14:51,992 --> 00:14:53,758
AND THE AEROS ARE OFFERING THEM

294
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:56,093
$100,000 EACH
TO PLAY HOCKEY.

295
00:14:56,129 --> 00:14:57,361
HELL, THAT'S
AS MUCH AS I MADE

296
00:14:57,430 --> 00:15:00,932
PLAYING 25 YEARS FOR DETROIT.

297
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:04,102
IS COLLEEN BEHIND THIS?

298
00:15:06,306 --> 00:15:08,238
LET'S LEAVE MY WIFE
OUT OF THIS.

299
00:15:08,275 --> 00:15:12,377
I WISH I COULD.

300
00:15:12,512 --> 00:15:13,845
I KNOW IT'S BEEN YOUR DREAM

301
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:17,448
TO SEE YOUR SONS FOLLOW YOU
AS A RED WING,

302
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,050
SO I'LL BE BLUNT.

303
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:23,187
IF THEY SIGN
WITH THE WHA,

304
00:15:23,323 --> 00:15:24,923
THEY'RE THROWING AWAY
THAT DREAM,

305
00:15:25,058 --> 00:15:28,059
AND JEOPARDIZING THEIR CHANCES
OF EVER PLAYING IN THE NHL

306
00:15:28,128 --> 00:15:29,127
AT ALL!

307
00:15:31,865 --> 00:15:33,865
WELL, I GOT OTHER DREAMS.

308
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:42,006
WE DONE, BRUCE?

309
00:15:46,079 --> 00:15:48,212
ARE WE CLEAR HERE

310
00:15:48,214 --> 00:15:50,114
WHAT YOU NEED TO DO WITH
YOUR BOYS, BIG FELLA?

311
00:15:51,117 --> 00:15:53,084
ABSOLUTELY.

312
00:15:57,490 --> 00:16:00,425
YOU'RE 45 YEARS OLD,

313
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:01,492
YOU'RE RIDDLED WITH ARTHRITIS,

314
00:16:01,528 --> 00:16:02,827
YOU'VE BROKEN MORE BONES

315
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:04,095
THAN EITHER ONE OF US
CAN REMEMBER--

316
00:16:04,097 --> 00:16:05,229
I KNOW.

317
00:16:05,365 --> 00:16:06,897
I KNOW HOW HARD
IT'S GONNA BE TO COME BACK.

318
00:16:06,967 --> 00:16:08,032
HARD?

319
00:16:08,068 --> 00:16:10,034
HONEY, AT YOUR AGE,
IT'S CRAZY.

320
00:16:10,169 --> 00:16:11,368
AND DANGEROUS.

321
00:16:11,404 --> 00:16:12,569
WHAT ABOUT NORRIS?

322
00:16:12,605 --> 00:16:14,305
HE'S GOING TO
BRAND YOU AS A TRAITOR?

323
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:16,307
AND WHAT ARE THE FANS
GOING TO SAY?

324
00:16:16,442 --> 00:16:17,908
I DON'T KNOW.

325
00:16:17,944 --> 00:16:19,977
I DON'T KNOW, BUT I THINK
IT'S WORTH THE RISK.

326
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,111
YOU KNOW IT'S ALWAYS
BEEN MY DREAM

327
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:23,314
TO PLAY WITH THE BOYS,

328
00:16:23,316 --> 00:16:26,184
AND TO START 'EM OFF RIGHT.

329
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:27,318
I KNOW,

330
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:28,386
BUT IS IT
THEIR DREAM, TOO?

331
00:16:28,455 --> 00:16:30,321
YEAH. ABSOLUTELY.

332
00:16:30,456 --> 00:16:31,856
WE TALK ABOUT IT ALL THE TIME,

333
00:16:31,925 --> 00:16:34,125
PLAYING SHINNY,
AND PLAYING CHARITY GAMES.

334
00:16:34,194 --> 00:16:36,260
WE TALK ABOUT IT ALL THE TIME.

335
00:16:38,631 --> 00:16:41,132
YOU'RE ASKING
A LOT OF ME, TOO, YOU KNOW?

336
00:16:41,267 --> 00:16:44,936
TO JUST GIVE UP EVERYTHING
I'VE BUILT HERE?

337
00:16:44,938 --> 00:16:46,336
A LOT OF CATHY AND MUZZ, TOO.

338
00:16:46,373 --> 00:16:48,473
I KNOW.

339
00:16:49,542 --> 00:16:52,410
I KNOW I AM.

340
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:57,014
BUT...

341
00:16:57,050 --> 00:17:01,218
ISN'T THIS
WHAT AN ADVENTURE IS?

342
00:17:01,287 --> 00:17:04,355
ISN'T THIS WHAT YOU SAID
THAT WE HAD TO LOOK FORWARD TO?

343
00:17:04,490 --> 00:17:06,224
[CHUCKLES RUEFULLY]

344
00:17:06,359 --> 00:17:07,959
LORD, I DIDN'T MEAN THIS.

345
00:17:12,399 --> 00:17:13,531
I'M MOVING TO TEXAS.

346
00:17:15,568 --> 00:17:16,434
I'LL CALL THE KIDS
IN TO EXPLAIN.

347
00:17:16,503 --> 00:17:18,035
NO, NO, NO, NO.

348
00:17:18,038 --> 00:17:20,571
I WANT TO SURPRISE THEM.

349
00:17:25,512 --> 00:17:26,511
[SIGHS]

350
00:17:28,381 --> 00:17:29,380
HARV.

351
00:17:29,449 --> 00:17:30,448
GORDIE.

352
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:31,382
FOXY.

353
00:17:31,451 --> 00:17:32,583
GORDIE.

354
00:17:34,454 --> 00:17:35,519
[CLEARS THROAT]

355
00:17:35,588 --> 00:17:38,856
NOW, FOXY, WHAT WOULD YOU SAY...

356
00:17:38,925 --> 00:17:40,191
TO THREE HOWES

357
00:17:40,260 --> 00:17:43,961
COMING TO PLAY FOR YOU
IN HOUSTON THIS YEAR?

358
00:17:45,932 --> 00:17:46,998
[CATHY]: WHAT?

359
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,534
YOU MEAN WE'RE MOVING TO TEXAS?

360
00:17:52,004 --> 00:17:54,939
[SCOFFS] I DON'T
BELIEVE THIS!

361
00:17:56,176 --> 00:17:57,475
DAD, IS THERE ANY MINOR HOCKEY
DOWN THERE AT ALL?

362
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:00,611
WE'LL SORT THAT OUT, SON.

363
00:18:02,148 --> 00:18:04,215
WELL, WHAT DO
MY NEW TEAMMATES SAY?

364
00:18:04,217 --> 00:18:06,150
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SEE THE OLD MAN

365
00:18:06,285 --> 00:18:08,418
LINING UP ALONGSIDE YOU
THIS YEAR?

366
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,354
YEAH. YEAH. SURE, DAD.

367
00:18:10,423 --> 00:18:12,523
IF YOU THINK IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

368
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,561
I DO.

369
00:18:16,696 --> 00:18:18,296
MARK, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

370
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:21,298
YEAH. YEAH,
SURE, DAD.

371
00:18:21,367 --> 00:18:22,333
YEAH.

372
00:18:24,070 --> 00:18:25,570
WELL, THAT'S
A POSITIVE ANSWER.

373
00:18:32,078 --> 00:18:33,311
IS ANYONE HERE EXCITED

374
00:18:33,313 --> 00:18:36,180
ABOUT THE FIRST
FATHER-AND-SON TEAM EVER?

375
00:18:38,051 --> 00:18:39,117
HELL, YEAH.

376
00:18:39,252 --> 00:18:40,184
YEAH.

377
00:18:40,319 --> 00:18:41,518
NICE, BILLY.

378
00:18:41,554 --> 00:18:43,254
HARV.

379
00:18:43,389 --> 00:18:44,655
ALL RIGHT, THEN,
LET'S MAKE THIS HAPPEN.

380
00:19:09,282 --> 00:19:12,416
MARK, I'M WORRIED
ABOUT DAD PLAYING AGAIN.

381
00:19:12,485 --> 00:19:14,418
I MEAN, FROM
WHAT I'VE SEEN,

382
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:17,287
THEY REALLY KNOW
HOW TO GOON IT UP IN THE WHA.

383
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:18,356
[CATHY]:
HEY, MARTY,

384
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:19,557
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA ASK FOR
IN YOUR CONTRACT?

385
00:19:19,692 --> 00:19:21,492
SOME LAME-O CAR?

386
00:19:21,561 --> 00:19:23,294
SHUT UP, CATHY.

387
00:19:23,429 --> 00:19:25,029
YOU SHUT UP.

388
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:26,764
I'M THE ONE'S GOTTA MOVE HERE
TO TEXAS 'CAUSE OF YOU TWO.

389
00:19:28,401 --> 00:19:29,433
I'M SERIOUS.

390
00:19:29,569 --> 00:19:30,568
I THINK HE COULD GET
REALLY HURT.

391
00:19:30,637 --> 00:19:32,236
HURT?

392
00:19:32,371 --> 00:19:33,304
HE COULD GET KILLED.

393
00:19:33,439 --> 00:19:35,239
HE'S 45, MARTY.

394
00:19:36,276 --> 00:19:38,376
SO, WHAT DO WE DO?

395
00:19:38,511 --> 00:19:39,544
I DON'T KNOW.

396
00:19:40,646 --> 00:19:43,047
HE'S SO EXCITED ABOUT IT.

397
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:44,181
LISTEN TO YOU TWO.

398
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:46,250
YOU'RE AFRAID OF
PLAYING WITH HIM.

399
00:19:46,385 --> 00:19:47,584
YOU KNEW
YOU'D BE COMPARED TO DAD

400
00:19:47,620 --> 00:19:49,120
IF YOU WERE STUPID ENOUGH
TO PLAY HOCKEY,

401
00:19:49,122 --> 00:19:52,690
WHICH APPARENTLY YOU ARE.

402
00:19:54,827 --> 00:19:56,127
HEY! STOP IT!

403
00:19:56,262 --> 00:19:57,061
STOP IT! STOP IT!
NO! STOP IT!

404
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,663
[SHRIEKING IN PROTEST]

405
00:19:58,798 --> 00:20:00,130
[BROTHERS LAUGHING]

406
00:20:00,166 --> 00:20:01,065
YOUR TURN, MUZZ!

407
00:20:01,201 --> 00:20:02,799
NOT COOL, GUYS!

408
00:20:02,835 --> 00:20:06,070
I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING!

409
00:20:06,072 --> 00:20:08,172
YOU WERE
THINKING IT!

410
00:20:15,348 --> 00:20:16,547
THANK YOU.

411
00:20:20,153 --> 00:20:21,786
AH, THANK YOU, JIM.

412
00:20:23,223 --> 00:20:26,223
YOU ARE YOUNGER THAN
MOST OF THE HOCKEY GMs

413
00:20:26,292 --> 00:20:27,625
I'M USED TO DEALING WITH.

414
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:30,160
WELL, I'LL TAKE THAT
AS A COMPLIMENT, MRS. HOWE.

415
00:20:30,196 --> 00:20:31,095
COLLEEN, PLEASE.

416
00:20:31,230 --> 00:20:32,163
HMM.

417
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:35,098
SO...

418
00:20:35,134 --> 00:20:37,768
WE HAVE A MARKETING DREAM HERE.

419
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:40,104
THE GREATEST PLAYER OF ALL TIME

420
00:20:40,173 --> 00:20:41,238
COMING BACK
TO PLAY WITH HIS SONS.

421
00:20:41,274 --> 00:20:43,707
I KNOW THE BOBBY HULL
SIGNING

422
00:20:43,776 --> 00:20:45,309
PUT THE WHA ON THE MAP, BUT...

423
00:20:45,311 --> 00:20:47,478
THIS IS BIGGER.

424
00:20:48,781 --> 00:20:50,114
JUST OUT OF CURIOSITY,

425
00:20:50,183 --> 00:20:52,116
HOW MUCH DID BOBBY MAKE
LAST YEAR?

426
00:20:53,252 --> 00:20:55,753
HULL IS 33,
YOUR HUSBAND IS 45.

427
00:20:57,290 --> 00:20:58,322
OH, I KNOW,

428
00:20:58,358 --> 00:21:00,391
BUT AGE IS AN ATTITUDE, JIM.

429
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:03,060
PLUS, WE HAVE TO FACTOR IN
THE RISK TO MY HUSBAND,

430
00:21:03,129 --> 00:21:06,797
GIVING UP A GUARANTEED CAREER
WITH THE RED WINGS

431
00:21:06,866 --> 00:21:10,835
TO COME AND HELP YOU SUPPORT
YOUR BRAND-NEW LEAGUE.

432
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:13,470
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

433
00:21:13,539 --> 00:21:17,541
HOW MUCH IS ALL THAT
WORTH TO YOU?

434
00:21:17,577 --> 00:21:19,744
I DON'T KNOW,
COLLEEN,

435
00:21:19,746 --> 00:21:23,180
BUT I HAVE A FEELING
YOU'RE GOING TO TELL ME.

436
00:21:24,517 --> 00:21:25,549
I HAVE AN IDEA.

437
00:21:26,619 --> 00:21:29,220
WHY DON'T WE EACH
WRITE DOWN A NUMBER,

438
00:21:29,222 --> 00:21:30,620
JUST KIND OF
SEE WHERE WE'RE AT.

439
00:21:30,657 --> 00:21:32,256
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

440
00:21:34,627 --> 00:21:35,426
ALL RIGHT.

441
00:21:35,561 --> 00:21:37,528
OKAY.

442
00:21:44,771 --> 00:21:46,370
THANK YOU.

443
00:22:08,928 --> 00:22:12,463
YOURS IS A LOT HIGHER, COLLEEN.

444
00:22:15,601 --> 00:22:17,868
I CAN'T DO SPOT DUTY, FOXY.

445
00:22:17,904 --> 00:22:20,671
IF I'M COMING BACK,
I'M COMING BACK TO PLAY.

446
00:22:20,806 --> 00:22:23,407
UNDERSTOOD.

447
00:22:23,409 --> 00:22:24,408
NOW, WHAT ABOUT

448
00:22:24,444 --> 00:22:26,210
THIS HOUSTON OWNER?

449
00:22:26,279 --> 00:22:27,345
CAN WE TRUST HIM?

450
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,746
HE'S ON HIS WAY OUT,

451
00:22:28,748 --> 00:22:30,281
BUT WE GOT GOOD
LOCAL OWNERSHIP COMING IN.

452
00:22:30,416 --> 00:22:31,348
OH, LORDY.

453
00:22:31,384 --> 00:22:33,217
ARE THE CHECKS GONNA CASH?

454
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:34,551
YOURS WILL.

455
00:22:34,587 --> 00:22:37,521
MINE? I DON'T KNOW.

456
00:22:41,260 --> 00:22:45,563
I SPENT 25 YEARS
BUILDING MY REPUTATION.

457
00:22:45,565 --> 00:22:49,166
I'M PUTTING ALL THAT
ON THE LINE HERE.

458
00:22:49,235 --> 00:22:52,770
NOW, YOU HAD MY BACK
AS A TEAMMATE.

459
00:22:52,772 --> 00:22:54,905
DO YOU STILL HAVE IT?

460
00:22:54,974 --> 00:22:58,442
YOU KNOW I DO, GORDIE.

461
00:22:58,478 --> 00:22:59,910
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

462
00:22:59,946 --> 00:23:01,511
OVER HERE, MR. HOWE!

463
00:23:01,547 --> 00:23:03,580
<i>[NEWS REPORT]: MR. HOCKEY
IS LEAVING DETROIT.</i>

464
00:23:03,649 --> 00:23:05,248
<i>GORDIE HOWE IS COMING
OUT OF RETIREMENT AT AGE 45</i>

465
00:23:05,284 --> 00:23:06,983
<i>TO STRAP ON THE BLADES...</i>

466
00:23:07,019 --> 00:23:08,319
<i>NOT FOR HIS RED WINGS,</i>

467
00:23:08,454 --> 00:23:09,386
<i>BUT TO LINE UP
ALONGSIDE HIS SONS,</i>

468
00:23:09,422 --> 00:23:10,588
<i>MARTY AND MARK HOWE,</i>

469
00:23:10,723 --> 00:23:11,855
<i>AS A HOUSTON AERO</i>

470
00:23:11,924 --> 00:23:14,358
<i>IN THE NEW
WORLD HOCKEY ASSOCIATION--</i>

471
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:21,598
ALL OF THEM.

472
00:23:21,667 --> 00:23:24,268
TAKE THEM ALL DOWN!

473
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:27,404
[RADIO INTERVIEW]:<i> IS THIS
SOME KIND OF PUBLICITY STUNT?</i>

474
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,806
[COMMENTATOR]:<i> IS IT A STUNT?</i>

475
00:23:28,808 --> 00:23:30,207
<i>HONESTLY, I CAN'T SEE
GORDIE HOWE DOING THAT.</i>

476
00:23:30,342 --> 00:23:31,942
<i>BUT HOW DESPERATE
MUST THIS NEW LEAGUE BE</i>

477
00:23:32,077 --> 00:23:34,678
<i>TO SIGN A RETIRED
45-YEAR-OLD PLAYER</i>

478
00:23:34,680 --> 00:23:36,480
<i>AND TWO UNDER-AGED KIDS?</i>

479
00:23:36,615 --> 00:23:38,449
[♪♪]

480
00:23:41,821 --> 00:23:42,787
[FLASHBULB POPS]

481
00:23:49,328 --> 00:23:51,395
[QUIET CHATTING]
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

482
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:53,964
TOSS ME THAT?

483
00:23:54,099 --> 00:23:56,634
I'M MARTY HOWE.

484
00:23:56,769 --> 00:23:57,901
JOHN.

485
00:23:57,970 --> 00:23:59,703
I, UH...

486
00:23:59,739 --> 00:24:03,373
I GOTTA SAY, IT'S AN HONOR
TO BE PLAYING WITH YOU, GORDIE.

487
00:24:03,443 --> 00:24:04,774
WELL, THANK YOU, STAN,

488
00:24:04,811 --> 00:24:06,376
BUT YOU'RE
PLAYING AGAINST ME

489
00:24:06,412 --> 00:24:08,512
TILL I MAKE THE TEAM.

490
00:24:08,548 --> 00:24:10,314
[DOOR SQUEAKS OPENS]

491
00:24:10,383 --> 00:24:12,383
HEY, NEW GUYS!

492
00:24:12,518 --> 00:24:14,852
[LAUGHING]
ALL RIGHT...

493
00:24:14,854 --> 00:24:16,320
FRESH MEAT.

494
00:24:16,389 --> 00:24:18,422
[CACKLING]

495
00:24:19,492 --> 00:24:21,525
WHAT WAS YOUR NAME
AGAIN, OLD-TIMER?

496
00:24:21,594 --> 00:24:23,794
HOWE.

497
00:24:23,796 --> 00:24:25,328
HOWE...

498
00:24:25,364 --> 00:24:27,397
HOWE. HOWE...

499
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:29,733
ANY RELATION TO SYD HOWE?

500
00:24:29,869 --> 00:24:32,002
[LAUGHTER]

501
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:36,006
NOW, THERE WAS A HOWE
OF A HOCKEY PLAYER!

502
00:24:36,042 --> 00:24:37,741
[LAUGHING]

503
00:24:37,777 --> 00:24:38,876
PLEASURE. PLEASURE.

504
00:24:38,945 --> 00:24:40,878
WHOA, BOYS!

505
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:41,812
I GOT ONE.

506
00:24:41,814 --> 00:24:42,947
[TEAM EXCLAIMS] WHOA! HEY!

507
00:24:43,082 --> 00:24:45,549
PRIZE COCKROACH
AT THE OLD SAM HOUSTON!

508
00:24:45,551 --> 00:24:46,550
KEEP THAT CRAP
AWAY FROM ME, SCHELLA.

509
00:24:46,586 --> 00:24:47,684
YOU KNOW I HATE THEM THINGS.

510
00:24:47,753 --> 00:24:49,887
IT'S A BIG FELLA!

511
00:24:50,022 --> 00:24:52,689
IT'S GOT AT LEAST SIX ELBOWS...

512
00:24:52,725 --> 00:24:55,292
IT'S A LITTLE
LONG IN THE TOOTH, THOUGH.

513
00:24:55,361 --> 00:24:56,627
CHECK IT OUT.

514
00:24:56,696 --> 00:24:58,062
WHAT DO YOU THINK
WE SHOULD CALL IT?

515
00:24:59,532 --> 00:25:01,031
WHY DON'T YOU CALL HIM GORDIE?

516
00:25:01,100 --> 00:25:02,366
[LAUGHTER]

517
00:25:02,368 --> 00:25:03,968
THERE YOU GO.

518
00:25:06,472 --> 00:25:07,504
SCHELLA...

519
00:25:07,540 --> 00:25:08,838
WHERE'S SMOKEY?

520
00:25:08,875 --> 00:25:09,706
SCHELLA! SCHELLA! SCHELLA!

521
00:25:09,775 --> 00:25:10,641
THIS ONE'S FOR YOU,
SMOKEY-BOY.

522
00:25:10,710 --> 00:25:12,710
SCHELLA!

523
00:25:12,845 --> 00:25:15,378
[LAUGHTER]

524
00:25:15,414 --> 00:25:16,380
COME ON, SMOKEY!

525
00:25:16,449 --> 00:25:18,749
[TEAM CHEERING AND HECKLING]

526
00:25:37,403 --> 00:25:38,469
HE'S STILL GOT THE ELBOWS.

527
00:25:41,574 --> 00:25:42,773
[RICOCHETS OFF THE POST]

528
00:25:44,644 --> 00:25:45,542
[WHISTLE BLASTS]

529
00:25:45,578 --> 00:25:48,545
OKAY, BOYS,
BRING IT IN!

530
00:25:48,548 --> 00:25:50,948
[CRICKETS CHIRPING PEACEFULLY]

531
00:25:51,017 --> 00:25:52,015
[GASPS]

532
00:25:52,084 --> 00:25:55,119
WOW, WELL, THIS IS NICE.

533
00:25:58,891 --> 00:26:00,424
NOT MUCH TO
COMPLAIN ABOUT HERE,

534
00:26:00,426 --> 00:26:03,694
IS THERE, MISSY MUFFET?

535
00:26:03,829 --> 00:26:05,095
MEET THE NEIGHBORS.

536
00:26:05,097 --> 00:26:08,899
[CATTLE LOWING]

537
00:26:10,636 --> 00:26:12,036
[CHUCKLING]

538
00:26:12,038 --> 00:26:13,938
[WHISTLE BLASTS]
ON THE LINE!

539
00:26:27,853 --> 00:26:29,853
WELL, IT LOOKS LIKE
THE LEGS HAVE LOST A STEP.

540
00:26:29,989 --> 00:26:31,522
A STEP?

541
00:26:31,524 --> 00:26:35,392
LOOKS LIKE HE'S GONNA HAVE
A DAMN HEART ATTACK.

542
00:26:35,461 --> 00:26:37,695
[WHISTLE BLASTS]

543
00:26:57,216 --> 00:26:59,083
YOU OKAY, DAD?

544
00:26:59,218 --> 00:27:01,484
YOU LOOK AWFUL RED.

545
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:02,819
YEAH. IT'S JUST...

546
00:27:02,855 --> 00:27:06,690
IT'S JUST THE HEAT.

547
00:27:06,726 --> 00:27:08,692
AND IT'S GORDIE.

548
00:27:12,031 --> 00:27:13,964
ON THE LINE!

549
00:27:16,569 --> 00:27:18,035
LET'S GO!

550
00:27:25,110 --> 00:27:26,042
[WHISTLE BLASTS]

551
00:27:26,078 --> 00:27:27,578
GO!

552
00:27:38,224 --> 00:27:40,190
DAD, IT'S TIME
FOR DINNER.

553
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:41,525
[MUMBLES]

554
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:42,992
DADDY?

555
00:27:43,029 --> 00:27:44,128
ARE YOU OKAY?

556
00:27:44,130 --> 00:27:45,062
[GROANS]

557
00:27:45,064 --> 00:27:46,930
OH, LORD.

558
00:27:46,999 --> 00:27:49,466
I WAS SUCKING WIND
OUT THERE TODAY, MISSY.

559
00:27:49,535 --> 00:27:50,634
IT WAS NOT PRETTY.

560
00:27:52,772 --> 00:27:53,937
[MARTY]: HONESTLY, MOM,

561
00:27:54,073 --> 00:27:55,806
I THOUGHT HE WAS
GONNA HAVE A HEART ATTACK.

562
00:27:55,941 --> 00:27:59,810
I MEAN, WE ALL DID.

563
00:28:02,081 --> 00:28:03,614
WHAT'S FOR DINNER?

564
00:28:03,616 --> 00:28:05,682
NOTHING.
COME ON, LET'S GO.

565
00:28:05,718 --> 00:28:06,817
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

566
00:28:06,819 --> 00:28:08,085
WE'RE GOING TO THE DOCTOR.

567
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:09,687
YOU NEED YOUR HEART
AND BLOOD PRESSURE CHECKED.

568
00:28:09,822 --> 00:28:10,754
NO, NO, NO, NO.

569
00:28:10,889 --> 00:28:12,756
I'VE ALREADY HAD
MY PHYSICAL.

570
00:28:12,891 --> 00:28:13,957
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

571
00:28:14,093 --> 00:28:15,759
HONEY.

572
00:28:15,828 --> 00:28:17,961
PLEASE? FOR ME?

573
00:28:24,236 --> 00:28:25,636
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

574
00:28:38,284 --> 00:28:40,217
HE'S ON YOUR WING!
ON YOUR WING!

575
00:28:58,937 --> 00:29:00,003
IT'S BEEN A WEEK.

576
00:29:00,039 --> 00:29:02,272
HE'S NOT GETTING ANY BETTER.

577
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:05,008
YOU KNOW, I MEAN,
IT COULD BE HE'S JUST TOO OLD.

578
00:29:05,010 --> 00:29:07,111
HE MAY NOT EVEN
MAKE THE TEAM.

579
00:29:08,714 --> 00:29:12,382
[SNORING]

580
00:29:14,687 --> 00:29:16,386
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

581
00:29:37,276 --> 00:29:39,777
I THINK I'VE MADE

582
00:29:39,912 --> 00:29:43,647
THE BIGGEST MISTAKE
OF MY LIFE.

583
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:46,984
SO WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO?

584
00:29:49,822 --> 00:29:51,255
FOXY DOESN'T THINK

585
00:29:51,390 --> 00:29:54,391
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE
THE LINE-UP.

586
00:29:56,896 --> 00:29:57,928
YOU NEED
TO LET ME KNOW

587
00:29:58,063 --> 00:29:59,929
WHEN IT'S TIME
TO CALL IT QUITS.

588
00:29:59,965 --> 00:30:02,399
OKAY?

589
00:30:46,412 --> 00:30:49,713
SO, I HEAR I'M NOT GONNA
MAKE YOUR TEAM.

590
00:30:49,849 --> 00:30:51,047
WELL, WE'RE GOING TO
TWO PRACTICES A DAY.

591
00:30:51,083 --> 00:30:52,182
YOU THINK YOU CAN HANDLE THAT?

592
00:30:52,184 --> 00:30:54,851
OH, YEAH.

593
00:30:54,854 --> 00:30:56,286
OR MAYBE I'LL JUST DIE.

594
00:30:58,424 --> 00:31:00,056
YOU STILL GOT MY BACK, FOXY?

595
00:31:00,125 --> 00:31:01,325
YEAH.

596
00:31:02,394 --> 00:31:03,794
LAST I HEARD,

597
00:31:03,796 --> 00:31:05,162
HOCKEY'S A TEAM SPORT,
THOUGH, GORDIE.

598
00:31:07,366 --> 00:31:10,267
YOU'RE AN EASY ONE TO HATE.

599
00:32:09,328 --> 00:32:10,326
OH!
[SMACKS HAND]

600
00:32:10,362 --> 00:32:12,896
THE BANANAS
ARE FOR YOU, HONEY.

601
00:32:30,482 --> 00:32:32,082
WHOA!

602
00:32:32,217 --> 00:32:33,483
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

603
00:32:33,552 --> 00:32:35,418
HEY, MARK!

604
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:38,188
IT'S ABOUT TIME YOU
BURIED ONE OF THOSE.

605
00:32:41,894 --> 00:32:43,226
SORRY, COACH.

606
00:32:43,295 --> 00:32:44,561
I GOT ANOTHER MIGRAINE.

607
00:32:47,366 --> 00:32:51,234
WHAT'S UP WITH THE KID
AND THE MIGRAINES?

608
00:32:51,236 --> 00:32:53,837
WELL, HE'S SENSITIVE,
LIKE HIS OLD MAN.

609
00:32:53,972 --> 00:32:55,105
[CHUCKLES]

610
00:32:55,174 --> 00:32:56,440
WHY DON'T YOU TRY
SHOVELING A LITTLE SUGAR

611
00:32:56,442 --> 00:32:57,975
ALONG WITH THE SAND
AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS?

612
00:33:00,279 --> 00:33:03,179
GEEZ, GORD, THAT WAS
A PRETTY GOOD SHIFT.

613
00:33:03,215 --> 00:33:04,314
THAT'S LITTLE ENOUGH.

614
00:33:06,518 --> 00:33:08,185
DON'T WORRY,
YOU MADE IT.

615
00:33:08,187 --> 00:33:11,555
THE BOYS ARE
GONNA MAKE IT, TOO.

616
00:33:15,327 --> 00:33:16,459
OKAY!

617
00:33:16,528 --> 00:33:18,394
LET'S PLAY SOME HOCKEY!

618
00:33:18,430 --> 00:33:20,430
I'M GONNA STAPLE YOU
THIS TIME, STANNY.

619
00:33:27,506 --> 00:33:29,139
THANKS FOR THE TIPS,
MR. HARVEY.

620
00:33:29,208 --> 00:33:30,940
HEY, ANYTIME, KID.

621
00:33:30,976 --> 00:33:34,011
I'LL TEACH YOU
WHATEVER I CAN REMEMBER.

622
00:33:34,146 --> 00:33:39,950
NOW, IT'S TIME FOR YOU AND I
TO GO HIT THE BAR.

623
00:33:39,952 --> 00:33:43,086
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
ON THE WAGON.

624
00:33:43,122 --> 00:33:44,821
I AM.

625
00:33:44,956 --> 00:33:46,823
BUT I STILL LIKE
THE SMELL.

626
00:33:46,958 --> 00:33:48,424
YOU GOT ANY MONEY
ON YOU, ROOK?

627
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:49,959
YEAH.

628
00:33:50,029 --> 00:33:51,027
GOOD.

629
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:52,896
YOU'RE GONNA
NEED A LOT.

630
00:33:52,898 --> 00:33:54,931
[CROWD CHEERING AND SHOUTING]

631
00:34:03,108 --> 00:34:04,974
WHO ARE THE
LOUDMOUTHS TONIGHT?

632
00:34:05,010 --> 00:34:06,109
HOCKEY PLAYERS.

633
00:34:06,178 --> 00:34:07,310
OH, GOD.

634
00:34:07,379 --> 00:34:09,446
I HEAR THEY'RE DUMBER
THAN RODEO COWBOYS,

635
00:34:09,448 --> 00:34:11,448
AND THAT'S SOME DUMB.

636
00:34:11,517 --> 00:34:13,450
WHAT'LL YOU HAVE?

637
00:34:13,519 --> 00:34:15,384
I'LL HAVE 13 RYES, DOUBLES,

638
00:34:15,421 --> 00:34:16,653
13 JACKS, ALSO DOUBLES,

639
00:34:16,655 --> 00:34:18,922
AND 26 DRAFTS.

640
00:34:18,991 --> 00:34:20,456
ARE YOU AN ALCOHOLIC?

641
00:34:20,492 --> 00:34:21,991
NO, THEY'RE FOR, UH,

642
00:34:22,061 --> 00:34:25,261
ME AND THE OTHER
DUMB HOCKEY PLAYERS.

643
00:34:25,297 --> 00:34:26,996
WELL, PARDON
MY FOOT IN THE MOUTH.

644
00:34:27,032 --> 00:34:30,033
NO NEED. IT'S TRUE.

645
00:34:32,104 --> 00:34:33,069
MARY FROM HOUSTON.

646
00:34:33,072 --> 00:34:36,273
MARTY FROM DETROIT.

647
00:34:36,275 --> 00:34:38,275
AND YOU'RE REALLY
A HOCKEY PLAYER?

648
00:34:38,277 --> 00:34:40,644
I REALLY AM, MARY FROM HOUSTON.

649
00:34:42,481 --> 00:34:44,414
[SMOKEY]: PICK UP THE CHICK
ON YOUR OWN TIME, KID!

650
00:34:44,416 --> 00:34:47,683
YOU'RE ON OUR DIME TONIGHT!

651
00:34:47,719 --> 00:34:49,486
[LAUGHTER]

652
00:35:01,032 --> 00:35:03,500
COME ON.

653
00:35:03,502 --> 00:35:04,701
COME ON, ROOKIE.

654
00:35:04,703 --> 00:35:06,536
SAME AGAIN, KID.
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

655
00:35:10,375 --> 00:35:12,576
SAME AGAIN, PLEASE.

656
00:35:18,684 --> 00:35:20,117
CHEERS.

657
00:35:24,189 --> 00:35:25,321
I KNOW IT'S ONLY
AN EXHIBITION GAME,

658
00:35:25,357 --> 00:35:26,522
BUT I CAN'T BELIEVE

659
00:35:26,558 --> 00:35:27,924
WE'RE PLAYING AGAINST
BOBBY HULL TONIGHT.

660
00:35:27,993 --> 00:35:29,125
YOU'LL BELIEVE IT

661
00:35:29,194 --> 00:35:30,393
WHEN HE DEKES YOU
OUT OF YOUR SKATES.

662
00:35:30,429 --> 00:35:32,195
HULL CAN BEAT YOU
FORE AND BACKHAND,

663
00:35:32,197 --> 00:35:34,197
AND HE'S TOO STRONG
TO KNOCK OFF THE PUCK.

664
00:35:34,266 --> 00:35:35,265
DO YOU GUYS
ALWAYS

665
00:35:35,267 --> 00:35:36,532
HAVE TO TALK
ABOUT HOCKEY?

666
00:35:36,568 --> 00:35:38,135
IT'S JUST FIGURE SKATING
WITH TWIGS, YOU KNOW?

667
00:35:38,236 --> 00:35:39,269
WHERE'D YOU GET
THAT CRAP FROM?

668
00:35:39,271 --> 00:35:40,470
TOMMY.

669
00:35:40,472 --> 00:35:41,470
WHO'S TOMMY?

670
00:35:41,507 --> 00:35:42,538
A FRIEND AT SCHOOL.

671
00:35:42,574 --> 00:35:43,473
HE PLAYS FOOTBALL.

672
00:35:43,608 --> 00:35:46,275
I'D LIKE TO MEET
THIS TOMMY.

673
00:35:46,311 --> 00:35:48,712
I'M SURE YOU WOULD, DAD.

674
00:35:55,254 --> 00:35:58,622
YOU SHOULD JUST BE HAPPY
THAT SHE'S MET A FRIEND.

675
00:35:58,624 --> 00:36:00,090
I'M HAPPY.

676
00:36:00,092 --> 00:36:02,292
SHE CAN COMPLAIN
TO HIM NOW.

677
00:36:02,427 --> 00:36:03,560
MARTY MADE A FRIEND TOO.

678
00:36:03,629 --> 00:36:05,028
GOT HER PHONE NUMBER.

679
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:06,730
WHAT'S THIS?

680
00:36:07,799 --> 00:36:09,399
NOTHING.

681
00:36:13,238 --> 00:36:14,571
[ORGAN PLAYING]

682
00:36:14,706 --> 00:36:16,506
SO, AM I GONNA HAVE TO
GO TO EVERY GAME?

683
00:36:16,575 --> 00:36:19,042
EVEN THESE PHONY
EXHIBITION ONES?

684
00:36:19,044 --> 00:36:20,510
YUP.

685
00:36:20,579 --> 00:36:22,979
WE'RE THE FIRST FAMILY
OF HOCKEY HERE.

686
00:36:23,114 --> 00:36:24,046
AND IT WOULDN'T HURT YOU

687
00:36:24,082 --> 00:36:26,349
TO SMILE ONCE
IN A WHILE, TOO.

688
00:36:26,351 --> 00:36:28,118
[LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY]

689
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:30,287
[WHISTLE BLASTS]

690
00:36:34,393 --> 00:36:37,060
THIS IS MY LEAGUE,
OLD MAN.

691
00:36:39,164 --> 00:36:40,196
[CROWD CHEERING]

692
00:36:40,232 --> 00:36:43,500
[♪♪]

693
00:36:56,682 --> 00:36:58,415
[GOAL HORN BLARES]

694
00:36:58,417 --> 00:37:00,483
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

695
00:37:02,387 --> 00:37:05,755
<i>GOAL SCORED BY NUMBER 9,
GORDIE HOWE!</i>

696
00:37:05,757 --> 00:37:07,823
<i>ASSISTED BY NUMBER 4,
MARK HOWE,</i>

697
00:37:07,859 --> 00:37:10,626
<i>AT 27 SECONDS
IN THE FIRST PERIOD.</i>

698
00:37:10,662 --> 00:37:11,694
THAT'S A GOOD
THING, OKAY?

699
00:37:11,730 --> 00:37:13,229
OKAY.

700
00:37:13,232 --> 00:37:14,097
[HULL]: REMEMBER, YOU PLAY
THAT DEEP ALL NIGHT,

701
00:37:14,233 --> 00:37:18,435
HE'LL GO THERE ON YOU.

702
00:37:18,437 --> 00:37:20,303
WHOSE LEAGUE
IS IT, BOBBY?

703
00:37:29,248 --> 00:37:30,547
[GASPING]

704
00:37:38,156 --> 00:37:39,789
DAD!

705
00:37:39,858 --> 00:37:40,857
NO...

706
00:37:40,859 --> 00:37:42,792
BREAK IT UP, GUYS.

707
00:37:42,828 --> 00:37:45,562
[CROWD CHEERING AND BOOING]

708
00:37:47,466 --> 00:37:49,332
BLUE, YOU'RE GOING
TO THE BOX.

709
00:37:49,368 --> 00:37:51,401
PULL UP YOUR SKIRT, HOWE!

710
00:37:51,470 --> 00:37:53,336
LITTLE BABY,
WHERE'S YOUR BOTTLE?

711
00:37:53,471 --> 00:37:55,138
THEY STILL CHANGING
YOUR DIAPER, TOO, MARK?

712
00:37:55,140 --> 00:37:56,473
HUH?

713
00:37:56,475 --> 00:37:58,842
[TEAM MURMURING ENCOURAGEMENTS]

714
00:38:02,881 --> 00:38:05,081
[RADIO PLAYS]

715
00:38:05,216 --> 00:38:08,284
HEY, LISTEN, GORDIE.

716
00:38:08,320 --> 00:38:12,688
YOU CAN'T-- YOU CAN'T BE
FIGHTING OUR BATTLES FOR US.

717
00:38:12,724 --> 00:38:14,691
IT'S EMBARRASSING.

718
00:38:16,595 --> 00:38:17,694
I'M GORDIE
WHEN THEY PLAY IT STRAIGHT,

719
00:38:17,763 --> 00:38:19,529
AND I'M YOUR DAD
WHEN THEY PLAY IT DIRTY.

720
00:38:21,366 --> 00:38:22,698
PULL UP
YOUR PANTS, LADIES!

721
00:38:22,734 --> 00:38:24,700
DRINKS ARE ON ME
TONIGHT, HOUSTON.

722
00:38:24,736 --> 00:38:28,104
[TEAM CHEERING]
THIS GUY. LOOK AT THIS GUY!

723
00:38:28,173 --> 00:38:30,440
WELL, ME
AND MY WHA PAYCHECK, THAT IS.

724
00:38:30,575 --> 00:38:31,307
[LAUGHTER]

725
00:38:31,376 --> 00:38:32,509
CAN YOU AFFORD IT, BOBBY?

726
00:38:32,511 --> 00:38:36,179
MIGHT HAVE TO SELL
