970
00:50:01,599 --> 00:50:03,466
YOU'RE A DIRTY OLD MAN, HOWE!

971
00:50:03,468 --> 00:50:08,270
I'LL TAKE YOU ON!
I'LL TAKE YOU ALL ON!

972
00:50:08,272 --> 00:50:09,271
I THOUGHT MINNESOTA

973
00:50:09,307 --> 00:50:11,273
WAS THE FRIENDLY
SWEDISH STATE.

974
00:50:11,409 --> 00:50:14,877
BOYS, WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU HAD A HAIRCUT?

975
00:50:15,012 --> 00:50:18,414
IT'S ABOUT TIME
FOR A TRIM, ISN'T IT?

976
00:50:18,416 --> 00:50:19,481
DON'T LOOK AT ME.

977
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:23,352
YOU TWO DON'T WANT
MY PROTECTION.

978
00:50:23,354 --> 00:50:25,654
[♪♪]

979
00:50:28,426 --> 00:50:29,625
[RADIO SHOW CALLER]:
<i>I CAN'T BELIEVE HOW WELL</i>

980
00:50:29,627 --> 00:50:30,493
<i>THE OLD GUY'S
PLAYING OUT THERE.</i>

981
00:50:30,628 --> 00:50:31,960
<i>I'M TELLING YOU,</i>

982
00:50:31,996 --> 00:50:33,295
<i>GORDIE'S PLAYING
BETTER THAN HE DID</i>

983
00:50:33,331 --> 00:50:34,964
<i>WITH THE RED WINGS
BACK IN THE MID-'60s.</i>

984
00:50:34,966 --> 00:50:36,565
<i>HE'S DOMINATING THE ICE!</i>

985
00:50:36,567 --> 00:50:38,100
[RADIO HOST]:<i> I'VE GOT TO
AGREE WITH YOU, FRIEND.</i>

986
00:50:38,136 --> 00:50:39,368
[CALLER]:
<i>AND WHAT AMAZES ME</i>

987
00:50:39,370 --> 00:50:40,836
<i>IS THAT HOWE'S DOING IT
WITH THESE KIDS.</i>

988
00:50:40,905 --> 00:50:42,838
<i>I MEAN, DOES THE YOUNG ONE
EVEN SHAVE YET?</i>

989
00:50:42,907 --> 00:50:43,972
[HOST]:
<i>LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,</i>

990
00:50:44,008 --> 00:50:45,374
<i>THOSE KIDS CAN REALLY PLAY.</i>

991
00:50:45,376 --> 00:50:46,975
<i>MARK MAY NOT SHAVE YET,</i>

992
00:50:47,045 --> 00:50:48,511
<i>BUT I THINK HE'S A SHOE-IN
FOR ROOKIE OF THE YEAR.</i>

993
00:50:48,646 --> 00:50:49,979
<i>NEXT CALLER.</i>

994
00:50:50,114 --> 00:50:51,313
LOOKIN' GOOD.

995
00:50:53,584 --> 00:50:54,517
WHO THE HECK
GAVE YOU PERMISSION

996
00:50:54,652 --> 00:50:56,385
TO TALK TO
THE WHA OWNERS?

997
00:50:56,520 --> 00:50:58,653
THEY WERE MERELY
INFORMAL CONVERSATIONS,

998
00:50:58,689 --> 00:50:59,855
NOTHING MORE.

999
00:50:59,990 --> 00:51:01,657
ABOUT A MERGER
WITH THE NHL?

1000
00:51:01,659 --> 00:51:03,325
THAT WAS PART OF IT, YES--

1001
00:51:03,461 --> 00:51:04,593
OVER MY DEAD BODY.

1002
00:51:04,662 --> 00:51:06,661
MERGER...

1003
00:51:06,697 --> 00:51:08,330
OUR REVENUES ARE DOWN,

1004
00:51:08,332 --> 00:51:11,000
AND THE WHA IS TURNING INTO
A SERIOUS DRAW, BRUCE!

1005
00:51:11,002 --> 00:51:13,869
IT'S A LEAGUE OF HAS-BEENS
AND NEVER-GONNA-BE'S!

1006
00:51:14,004 --> 00:51:16,338
IF YOU WANNA KEEP YOUR JOB HERE,
I'D SHUT UP NOW!

1007
00:51:16,407 --> 00:51:18,474
YOU DON'T NEED TO WRITE
THAT LAST SENTENCE DOWN.

1008
00:51:18,476 --> 00:51:21,177
PRESIDENT CAMPBELL
WILL GET THE GIST.

1009
00:51:25,950 --> 00:51:27,349
THE LIGHTS ARE OUT.

1010
00:51:27,385 --> 00:51:28,551
[TEAMMATES LAUGHING]

1011
00:51:28,686 --> 00:51:30,219
[BOYS SHOUTING IN ALARM]

1012
00:51:30,288 --> 00:51:31,553
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

1013
00:51:31,622 --> 00:51:33,221
[SMOKEY]: HEY,
WE GOT YOU, JUNIOR.

1014
00:51:33,257 --> 00:51:34,223
[CACKLING]

1015
00:51:34,225 --> 00:51:35,490
RELAX, ROOKIE.

1016
00:51:35,526 --> 00:51:37,960
TODAY, YOU BECOME A MAN,

1017
00:51:37,962 --> 00:51:39,428
OR AT LEAST
A HOUSTON AERO!

1018
00:51:39,430 --> 00:51:42,731
[LAUGHTER]

1019
00:51:51,008 --> 00:51:53,042
MARK GOT ANOTHER
MIGRAINE?

1020
00:51:53,044 --> 00:51:54,176
YEAH.

1021
00:51:54,311 --> 00:51:57,379
I CLOSED THE BLINDS
SO HE COULD SLEEP.

1022
00:52:02,453 --> 00:52:04,320
HE'S TICKED AT HIS TEAMMATES,
ISN'T HE?

1023
00:52:04,455 --> 00:52:05,654
I AM.

1024
00:52:05,690 --> 00:52:07,590
HOW COULD YOU LET THAT HAPPEN?

1025
00:52:07,592 --> 00:52:09,191
WAIT A SECOND,

1026
00:52:09,193 --> 00:52:10,325
YOU'RE THE ONE TELLING ME

1027
00:52:10,361 --> 00:52:11,526
I SHOULDN'T BE
THE BOYS' CHAPERONE.

1028
00:52:11,562 --> 00:52:15,331
IT IS BARBARIC.

1029
00:52:15,333 --> 00:52:17,199
YEAH.

1030
00:52:17,201 --> 00:52:19,201
YEAH, IT'S OLD-SCHOOL STUPID,

1031
00:52:19,203 --> 00:52:21,604
IT'S EVEN OLDER-SCHOOL THAN ME,

1032
00:52:21,606 --> 00:52:24,173
BUT IT MEANS SOMETHING.

1033
00:52:26,010 --> 00:52:29,011
THEIR TEAMMATES WANT TO KNOW
IF THEY CAN TRUST THE BOYS.

1034
00:52:29,146 --> 00:52:30,612
TRUST THEM?

1035
00:52:30,648 --> 00:52:33,415
THAT IS ABSOLUTELY RIDICULOUS.

1036
00:52:33,451 --> 00:52:36,685
THERE IS TWO TYPES
OF HOCKEY PLAYER, COLLEEN,

1037
00:52:36,754 --> 00:52:39,355
THERE IS THE THIN-SKINNED
AND THE THICK-SKINNED,

1038
00:52:39,357 --> 00:52:40,422
THE ONES WHO TURTLE,

1039
00:52:40,424 --> 00:52:41,624
AND THE ONES
WHO FIGHT BACK.

1040
00:52:41,626 --> 00:52:42,658
[SIGHS IN FRUSTRATION]

1041
00:52:44,362 --> 00:52:46,629
AND THEY'RE ASKING
WHICH ONE THE BOYS ARE.

1042
00:52:46,764 --> 00:52:50,499
WELL, I STILL DON'T APPROVE,

1043
00:52:50,634 --> 00:52:52,101
BUT I WOULD LIKE TO BE THERE

1044
00:52:52,236 --> 00:52:55,504
WHEN MY BOYS
GIVE THEM THEIR ANSWER.

1045
00:53:01,212 --> 00:53:02,644
[LAUGHTER]

1046
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:03,579
[MOCK SOBBING] AW, COACH,
DON'T MAKE ME SKATE!

1047
00:53:03,714 --> 00:53:05,714
AW, IT HURTS!
IT HURTS SO BAD!

1048
00:53:05,849 --> 00:53:07,315
[LAUGHS]

1049
00:53:07,351 --> 00:53:09,552
[CACKLING]

1050
00:53:10,654 --> 00:53:12,521
HOLY-- [YELPS IN ALARM]

1051
00:53:12,656 --> 00:53:13,722
[LAUGHTER]

1052
00:53:13,857 --> 00:53:15,457
GET 'EM OFF!

1053
00:53:15,493 --> 00:53:17,125
GET 'EM OFF!

1054
00:53:17,195 --> 00:53:19,194
[LAUGHTER]

1055
00:53:19,230 --> 00:53:20,195
DOES IT HURT, SMOKEY?

1056
00:53:20,198 --> 00:53:22,598
DOES IT HURT SO... BAD?

1057
00:53:22,600 --> 00:53:25,200
[LAUGHTER]

1058
00:53:25,236 --> 00:53:26,135
GOOD ONE, KID,
GOOD ONE.

1059
00:53:26,270 --> 00:53:29,071
NOW I GOTTA
BURN THE BAG.

1060
00:53:30,074 --> 00:53:32,141
[CHRISTMAS CAROLS PLAY]

1061
00:53:32,276 --> 00:53:34,009
[YOUNG MAN]:...YEAH,
I WOULD LOVE THAT.

1062
00:53:34,144 --> 00:53:36,679
[CATHY]: TONIGHT
WAS REALLY FUN.

1063
00:53:36,814 --> 00:53:38,280
YEAH, THANKS
FOR HAVING ME.

1064
00:53:38,415 --> 00:53:39,615
OH, ANY TIME.

1065
00:53:45,256 --> 00:53:46,021
[SLAMS DOOR]

1066
00:53:46,156 --> 00:53:47,189
[GASPING]

1067
00:53:48,326 --> 00:53:50,092
HI, DAD!

1068
00:53:50,161 --> 00:53:51,827
THIS MUST BE TOMMY.

1069
00:53:51,829 --> 00:53:53,228
YES.

1070
00:53:53,264 --> 00:53:55,096
I HEAR YOU DON'T
THINK TOO MUCH OF HOCKEY.

1071
00:53:55,132 --> 00:53:58,367
WELL, I-I NEVER
SEEN IT, SIR.

1072
00:53:58,436 --> 00:53:59,435
WELL, INVITE HIM
TO A GAME

1073
00:53:59,437 --> 00:54:01,169
SOME TIME, CATHY.

1074
00:54:01,239 --> 00:54:03,272
AND, UM, BE INSIDE
IN FIVE MINUTES,

1075
00:54:03,407 --> 00:54:05,140
OR THE YOUNG MAN
GETS A DATE WITH THE ELBOWS.

1076
00:54:11,582 --> 00:54:15,184
SO EMBARRASSING.

1077
00:54:15,186 --> 00:54:16,851
[WHISPERING] WOW...

1078
00:54:16,887 --> 00:54:21,657
WELL, YOUR DAD'S LIKE
CLINT EASTWOOD OR SOMETHING.

1079
00:54:24,595 --> 00:54:25,728
[LAUGHING]

1080
00:54:25,730 --> 00:54:27,596
OKAY, NOW,
SQUEEZE TOGETHER.

1081
00:54:27,598 --> 00:54:28,730
I'M BEING
SERIOUS, ACTUALLY.

1082
00:54:28,766 --> 00:54:30,465
ALL RIGHT.

1083
00:54:30,501 --> 00:54:32,334
SMILE, Y'ALL.

1084
00:54:32,370 --> 00:54:34,602
[SHUTTER CLICKS]

1085
00:54:34,639 --> 00:54:36,871
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S EAT, Y'ALL.

1086
00:54:36,907 --> 00:54:39,140
PASS... PASS THE BIG BIRD
DOWN HERE,

1087
00:54:39,176 --> 00:54:42,144
AND WE'LL CARVE HIM UP
REALLY GOOD.

1088
00:54:42,146 --> 00:54:44,746
[♪♪]

1089
00:54:44,782 --> 00:54:46,348
WE WILL SAY GRACE.

1090
00:54:46,483 --> 00:54:48,350
I THINK I'M GOING TO GET
A HEAD START ON CARVING THIS.

1091
00:54:48,386 --> 00:54:51,820
[♪♪]

1092
00:54:53,557 --> 00:54:54,690
HERE WE GO!

1093
00:54:59,463 --> 00:55:01,229
HI, LITTLE FELLA.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

1094
00:55:01,299 --> 00:55:02,297
[SPORTSCASTER]:
<i>WHAT A COMEBACK SEASON</i>

1095
00:55:02,366 --> 00:55:03,832
<i>MR. HOCKEY IS HAVING.</i>

1096
00:55:03,868 --> 00:55:05,834
<i>TURNING 46, AND NOW
LEADING THE LEAGUE IN SCORING.</i>

1097
00:55:05,870 --> 00:55:07,435
<i>I SAY GO, AEROS, GO!</i>

1098
00:55:07,471 --> 00:55:08,437
<i>GO, HOWES!</i>

1099
00:55:08,506 --> 00:55:09,638
<i>LET'S GET BEHIND THEM, Y'ALL.</i>

1100
00:55:09,640 --> 00:55:10,706
<i>NEXT CALLER.</i>

1101
00:55:10,775 --> 00:55:12,307
[CALLER]:<i> I DON'T THINK</i>

1102
00:55:12,310 --> 00:55:13,508
<i>THERE'S BEEN A FATHER-SON
TEAMMATE COMBO</i>

1103
00:55:13,577 --> 00:55:15,444
<i>IN ANY PROFESSIONAL SPORT,
HAS THERE?</i>

1104
00:55:15,579 --> 00:55:17,179
WELL, WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

1105
00:55:17,314 --> 00:55:20,449
DON'T LET IT GO TO
YOUR HEAD, OKAY, HONEY?

1106
00:55:20,451 --> 00:55:23,385
IT DOES NOT SAY
"GORIDE" HOWE.

1107
00:55:23,454 --> 00:55:25,587
YOU'RE UP THERE,
TOO, MISSUS.

1108
00:55:36,267 --> 00:55:38,400
[MARTY]:
UH-OH. HERE COMES TROUBLE.

1109
00:55:38,535 --> 00:55:40,668
CATHY AND HER NEW FRIEND.

1110
00:55:40,705 --> 00:55:42,270
[CATHY]: WHOO-HOO!

1111
00:55:42,306 --> 00:55:45,607
TEXAS FOREVER! WHOO!

1112
00:55:45,743 --> 00:55:48,210
SHE LOOKS
PRETTY HAPPY HERE.

1113
00:55:48,212 --> 00:55:49,945
YEAH.

1114
00:55:49,947 --> 00:55:53,849
I COULD SEE
MAKING HOUSTON MY HOME.

1115
00:55:56,954 --> 00:55:57,886
[CHUCKLES]

1116
00:56:02,826 --> 00:56:03,892
MARTY?

1117
00:56:04,027 --> 00:56:05,894
I NEED TO SPEAK WITH YOU
FOR A MOMENT.

1118
00:56:07,498 --> 00:56:08,830
WHAT'S UP?

1119
00:56:08,866 --> 00:56:09,898
FOXY JUST CALLED.

1120
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:11,567
HE NEEDS YOU
TO FIND DOUG HARVEY

1121
00:56:11,569 --> 00:56:12,901
AND BRING HIM
TO THE SAM HOUSTON.

1122
00:56:12,903 --> 00:56:14,369
HE'S BEEN DRINKING.

1123
00:56:14,372 --> 00:56:15,837
WHAT?

1124
00:56:15,906 --> 00:56:18,306
I GUESS HE'S FALLEN
OFF THE WAGON.

1125
00:56:18,342 --> 00:56:19,774
FOXY'S BEEN COVERING IT UP,

1126
00:56:19,810 --> 00:56:21,810
GETTING HIM SOBERED UP
FOR GAMES.

1127
00:56:23,013 --> 00:56:25,581
I WAS SUPPOSED TO TAKE
MARY OUT FOR SUPPER BEFORE--

1128
00:56:25,583 --> 00:56:27,683
WELL, I'M SORRY,
IT CAN'T BE HELPED, OKAY?

1129
00:56:31,122 --> 00:56:31,920
I GOTTA...

1130
00:56:31,956 --> 00:56:33,388
IT'S A TEAM THING.

1131
00:56:33,424 --> 00:56:35,457
I UNDERSTAND.

1132
00:56:35,459 --> 00:56:36,591
I'LL MAKE IT UP
TO YOU, OKAY?

1133
00:56:36,627 --> 00:56:38,260
I PROMISE.

1134
00:56:38,262 --> 00:56:39,528
LET'S GO.

1135
00:56:39,663 --> 00:56:40,863
[COLLEEN]: SORRY, MARY.

1136
00:56:40,998 --> 00:56:44,600
COMES WITH DATING
A HOCKEY PLAYER.

1137
00:57:09,059 --> 00:57:09,891
MR. HARVEY?

1138
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:11,826
HEY, KID, SIT DOWN.

1139
00:57:11,862 --> 00:57:16,431
JJ, A BEER FOR
MY YOUNG PROTEGE HERE.

1140
00:57:16,434 --> 00:57:19,300
MR. HARVEY, WE GOTTA
GET YOU TO THE SAM HOUSTON.

1141
00:57:19,336 --> 00:57:20,569
IT'S ALMOST GAME TIME.

1142
00:57:20,638 --> 00:57:23,638
WHY? I'M NOT PLAYING.

1143
00:57:23,707 --> 00:57:25,707
HARV, FOXY SENT ME.

1144
00:57:26,910 --> 00:57:29,577
WE GOTTA GET YOU
SOBERED UP.

1145
00:57:29,613 --> 00:57:30,779
DON'T LECTURE ME
ABOUT SOBER,

1146
00:57:30,914 --> 00:57:32,581
YOU LITTLE SNOT!

1147
00:57:34,918 --> 00:57:38,320
PLEASE, HARV, JUST...

1148
00:57:38,389 --> 00:57:39,788
JUST COME WITH ME, OKAY?

1149
00:57:45,863 --> 00:57:46,862
[SIGHS]

1150
00:57:46,931 --> 00:57:48,797
I'LL BE IN THE CAR.

1151
00:58:17,661 --> 00:58:19,561
YOU SEEM PRETTY
PLEASED WITH YOURSELF.

1152
00:58:19,630 --> 00:58:21,530
I'M READING HERE, PLEASE.

1153
00:58:26,470 --> 00:58:28,537
[SMACKS TABLE ANGRILY]

1154
00:58:31,542 --> 00:58:32,608
GORDIE?

1155
00:58:34,712 --> 00:58:36,578
[MARK STRUMMING GUITAR]

1156
00:58:36,713 --> 00:58:37,846
WHAT THE HECK IS THIS?

1157
00:58:37,915 --> 00:58:39,447
"I KNEW MY DAD
WAS AN OLD MAN,

1158
00:58:39,517 --> 00:58:42,718
I JUST DIDN'T KNOW
HE WAS A DIRTY OLD MAN TOO."

1159
00:58:42,853 --> 00:58:44,386
DAD, WHAT'S WRONG?
IT WAS A JOKE.

1160
00:58:44,455 --> 00:58:45,453
A JOKE?

1161
00:58:45,523 --> 00:58:46,788
WHAT THE HECK KIND OF THING
IS THAT TO SAY

1162
00:58:46,790 --> 00:58:47,856
ABOUT YOUR FATHER?

1163
00:58:47,858 --> 00:58:49,858
I WAS JUST TRYING TO EXPLAIN
TO THE REPORTER

1164
00:58:49,927 --> 00:58:53,528
HOW YOU PLAY WITH AN EDGE, AND--

1165
00:58:53,564 --> 00:58:55,330
I PLAY DIRTY?
IS THAT WHAT YOU THINK?

1166
00:58:55,399 --> 00:58:57,332
LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING ABOUT HOW I PLAY.

1167
00:58:57,401 --> 00:58:59,734
I'M A GOSH-DANG POLICEMAN
OUT THERE!

1168
00:59:00,804 --> 00:59:03,071
DAD, COME ON, YOU KNOW
YOU CROSS THE LINE SOMETIMES.

1169
00:59:03,140 --> 00:59:05,741
I CROSS THE LINE?
THERE IS NO LINE!

1170
00:59:05,743 --> 00:59:07,476
IF YOU LET THEM
THROW DIRT AT YOU,

1171
00:59:07,478 --> 00:59:09,143
THEY WILL KEEP DOING IT!

1172
00:59:09,179 --> 00:59:11,947
NOW, YOU APOLOGIZE.
RIGHT NOW.

1173
00:59:12,082 --> 00:59:13,015
HOW ABOUT ALL THE STUFF

1174
00:59:13,150 --> 00:59:14,549
THAT YOU AND MOM
TRY TO TEACH ME?

1175
00:59:14,552 --> 00:59:15,684
LIKE, "BE HUMBLE, KID,"

1176
00:59:15,819 --> 00:59:17,753
"THE MEEK INHERIT
THE EARTH, SON."

1177
00:59:17,755 --> 00:59:19,621
DO I JUST THROW
ALL THAT DIRT OUT NOW?

1178
00:59:19,690 --> 00:59:21,690
THE MEEK
MIGHT INHERIT THE EARTH.

1179
00:59:21,825 --> 00:59:23,458
I AM TALKING ABOUT THE ICE!

1180
00:59:35,072 --> 00:59:36,638
YOU NEED TO APOLOGIZE
TO YOUR FATHER.

1181
00:59:36,674 --> 00:59:37,706
NOW.

1182
00:59:37,841 --> 00:59:39,974
I DON'T KNOW, MOM,

1183
00:59:40,010 --> 00:59:42,711
IF I LET PEOPLE THROW DIRT,
THEY'LL JUST KEEP THROWING IT.

1184
00:59:42,780 --> 00:59:44,813
NOW.

1185
00:59:55,759 --> 00:59:59,661
THAT WAS A GREAT
COVER STORY, GORDIE.

1186
00:59:59,663 --> 01:00:01,396
WAS IT?

1187
01:00:01,465 --> 01:00:02,664
I DIDN'T FINISH IT.

1188
01:00:02,700 --> 01:00:03,832
YEAH, WELL,

1189
01:00:03,834 --> 01:00:05,000
I DON'T KNOW WHY
HE'S GOTTA RUN US DOWN.

1190
01:00:05,069 --> 01:00:06,768
HE DOESN'T KNOW WHAT
HE'S TALKING ABOUT.

1191
01:00:09,640 --> 01:00:11,139
[GORDIE]: WHAT'S TEDDY
GOT TO SAY NOW?

1192
01:00:11,141 --> 01:00:13,408
SOME B.S. ABOUT HOW WE CAN'T
BE MUCH OF A HOCKEY LEAGUE

1193
01:00:13,477 --> 01:00:16,077
IF WE'VE GOT A 45-YEAR-OLD
AS OUR LEADING SCORER.

1194
01:00:16,146 --> 01:00:17,545
[SMOKEY CACKLING]

1195
01:00:17,615 --> 01:00:18,547
MARKY, GREAT QUOTE
IN THE SPORTS MAG, BUDDY!

1196
01:00:18,682 --> 01:00:20,082
FREAKIN' HILARIOUS!

1197
01:00:20,084 --> 01:00:21,149
WHAT DID
HE SAY, SMOKEY?

1198
01:00:21,151 --> 01:00:22,818
I JUST READ IT IN THE CAN.

1199
01:00:22,953 --> 01:00:24,619
HE SAID, "I ALWAYS KNEW
MY DAD WAS AN OLD MAN,

1200
01:00:24,688 --> 01:00:27,022
I JUST DIDN'T KNOW HE WAS
A DIRTY OLD MAN."

1201
01:00:27,091 --> 01:00:29,691
[LAUGHTER]

1202
01:00:30,628 --> 01:00:32,127
DIRTY OLD MAN...

1203
01:00:34,698 --> 01:00:36,231
[CROWD CHEERING]

1204
01:00:42,239 --> 01:00:45,240
IT'S LIKE FOOTBALL
WITH SPEARS!

1205
01:00:58,055 --> 01:01:01,156
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1206
01:01:05,829 --> 01:01:06,795
COME ON, GORDIE.

1207
01:01:06,864 --> 01:01:07,929
TO THE BOX, GORD!

1208
01:01:07,965 --> 01:01:10,298
TO THE BOX,
TO THE BOX!

1209
01:01:13,037 --> 01:01:17,004
IN THE BOX, IN THE BOX.

1210
01:01:17,041 --> 01:01:18,673
YEAH, NOW THE REFS
ARE PROTECTING YOU,

1211
01:01:18,676 --> 01:01:20,742
HUH, GORD?

1212
01:01:20,778 --> 01:01:22,077
CHEAP SHOT, MAN.

1213
01:01:23,847 --> 01:01:26,148
NOT A WORD.

1214
01:01:31,288 --> 01:01:33,088
YOU GUYS SEEN HARV TONIGHT?

1215
01:01:33,157 --> 01:01:34,489
NO.

1216
01:01:34,624 --> 01:01:36,258
ANYONE?

1217
01:01:44,901 --> 01:01:47,636
[COLLEEN CLEARS HER THROAT]

1218
01:01:49,840 --> 01:01:52,274
[LOUDER] AHEM.

1219
01:01:56,980 --> 01:01:58,847
[SHARP KICK]

1220
01:02:05,656 --> 01:02:07,789
WHAT I MEANT TO SAY WAS

1221
01:02:07,791 --> 01:02:10,659
MY FATHER HAS A GREAT SENSE
OF JUSTICE ON THE ICE.

1222
01:02:10,794 --> 01:02:12,727
HE'S A POLICEMAN
OUT THERE,

1223
01:02:12,730 --> 01:02:15,664
LIKE... DIRTY HARRY.

1224
01:02:15,666 --> 01:02:17,065
[MUFFLED LAUGHTER]

1225
01:02:22,206 --> 01:02:24,539
IS THAT YOUR VERSION
OF AN APOLOGY?

1226
01:02:24,674 --> 01:02:27,242
YEAH.

1227
01:02:31,782 --> 01:02:34,249
ACCEPTED.

1228
01:02:38,856 --> 01:02:39,954
[COLLEEN SIGHS]

1229
01:02:40,023 --> 01:02:41,622
CAN I GET ANY MORE EGGS
FOR ANYONE?

1230
01:02:41,658 --> 01:02:43,024
- YEAH, SURE, MOM.
- OKAY. GREAT.

1231
01:02:43,093 --> 01:02:44,159
[♪♪]

1232
01:02:44,294 --> 01:02:45,760
[STATIC CRACKLES
AS SHE TUNES THE DIAL]

1233
01:02:45,796 --> 01:02:46,961
[SPORTS STATION
BROADCASTS HOCKEY GAME]

1234
01:02:46,997 --> 01:02:48,229
<i>...TRIPPING CALL ON THE AEROS</i>

1235
01:02:48,298 --> 01:02:50,098
<i>WITH LESS THAN TWO MINUTES
TO PLAY,</i>

1236
01:02:50,100 --> 01:02:53,034
<i>AND THE GAME OUT REACH FOR
THE HOST NEW ENGLAND WHALERS...</i>

1237
01:02:53,103 --> 01:02:55,102
CAN I LISTEN TO
SOME MUSIC NOW?

1238
01:02:55,139 --> 01:02:56,705
[SCOFFS]

1239
01:02:56,840 --> 01:02:59,241
<i>...HOWE AND LUND COME OUT
TO KILL THE PENALTY...</i>

1240
01:02:59,376 --> 01:03:00,642
YOU THINK YOU CAN
INFLUENCE THE GAME

1241
01:03:00,711 --> 01:03:02,243
JUST BY LISTENING
TO IT, DON'T YOU?

1242
01:03:02,312 --> 01:03:03,779
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

1243
01:03:03,914 --> 01:03:05,379
<i>...WHAT A DREAM SEASON
GORDIE HOWE HAS HAD.</i>

1244
01:03:05,415 --> 01:03:06,848
<i>100 POINTS.</i>

1245
01:03:06,884 --> 01:03:07,916
<i>THE LEAGUE-LEADING SCORER,</i>

1246
01:03:08,051 --> 01:03:09,383
<i>AND HIS FIRST-PLACE AEROS</i>

1247
01:03:09,419 --> 01:03:11,319
<i>ARE HEADING TO A PLAYOFF ROUND
AGAINST THE JETS</i>

1248
01:03:11,321 --> 01:03:12,721
<i>IN JUST TWO WEEKS...</i>

1249
01:03:12,856 --> 01:03:13,788
[BREATHING HARD]

1250
01:03:13,824 --> 01:03:15,123
YOU SO DO.

1251
01:03:15,258 --> 01:03:16,591
<i>[STICKS SLAPPING]
FACEOFF WON BY THE WHALERS.</i>

1252
01:03:16,726 --> 01:03:18,860
<i>GOES BACK TO SELLWOOD
AT THE POINT.</i>

1253
01:03:18,896 --> 01:03:20,995
<i>SELLWOOD LOOKING FOR
A SHOT ON NET,</i>

1254
01:03:21,031 --> 01:03:22,730
<i>THIS GUY CAN REALLY BOOM IT.</i>

1255
01:03:22,766 --> 01:03:24,332
<i>HOWE GOES DOWN
TO BLOCK THE SHOT!</i>

1256
01:03:24,368 --> 01:03:25,933
<i>OOH, THAT'S GOTTA HURT!</i>

1257
01:03:25,969 --> 01:03:27,668
<i>[WHISTLE BLASTS]</i>

1258
01:03:27,704 --> 01:03:33,041
<i>GORDIE HOWE IS DOWN ON THE ICE
AND GRIMACING WITH PAIN.</i>

1259
01:03:37,280 --> 01:03:39,748
<i>THE TRAINER BOBBY BROWN</i>

1260
01:03:39,750 --> 01:03:42,984
<i>COMES OFF THE BENCH
TO HELP HIM--</i>

1261
01:03:58,702 --> 01:04:00,835
ALL RIGHT, THANKS, BOB.

1262
01:04:00,904 --> 01:04:02,904
HE SAYS YOU GOT
A HAIRLINE FRACTURE.

1263
01:04:02,940 --> 01:04:04,239
YOU NEED TO KEEP WEIGHT OFF IT
FOR 10 DAYS,

1264
01:04:04,374 --> 01:04:05,506
AND YOU'LL NEED A CAST.

1265
01:04:05,576 --> 01:04:06,641
NOT BAD.

1266
01:04:06,776 --> 01:04:08,309
WELL, I'VE PLAYED WITH
A HAIRLINE FRACTURE BEFORE.

1267
01:04:08,378 --> 01:04:10,845
IT'S NOTHING, FOXY.

1268
01:04:10,914 --> 01:04:11,979
YEAH, BUT THERE'S NO POINT.

1269
01:04:12,015 --> 01:04:13,114
WE NEED YOU READY
FOR THE PLAYOFFS.

1270
01:04:13,183 --> 01:04:15,449
WHAT ABOUT
THE SCORING CHAMPIONSHIP?

1271
01:04:15,485 --> 01:04:17,652
WHAT ABOUT IT?

1272
01:04:17,721 --> 01:04:19,387
THERE'S EIGHT GAMES LEFT.

1273
01:04:19,456 --> 01:04:21,989
I'M ONLY SEVEN POINTS
AHEAD OF WALTON.

1274
01:04:22,025 --> 01:04:24,059
TELL SOMEONE WHO CARES, GORDIE.

1275
01:04:24,061 --> 01:04:26,728
YOU KNOW I HATE TO LOSE.

1276
01:04:26,730 --> 01:04:28,196
SO DO I.

1277
01:04:28,198 --> 01:04:29,798
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE NOT
IN MY LINE-UP TILL THE PLAYOFFS.

1278
01:04:29,800 --> 01:04:32,133
OH, YOU'RE EASY ONE TO HA--

1279
01:04:32,269 --> 01:04:33,268
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH,
I'M AN EASY ONE TO HATE.

1280
01:04:33,337 --> 01:04:34,903
I KNOW!

1281
01:04:44,948 --> 01:04:46,214
YEAH, GOOD SKATE TODAY, GUYS.

1282
01:04:46,283 --> 01:04:48,349
LOOKING GOOD.

1283
01:04:48,418 --> 01:04:50,785
[PLAYERS ALL CHATTING]

1284
01:04:52,489 --> 01:04:53,688
HEY, HARV!

1285
01:04:53,757 --> 01:04:55,957
WHERE YOU BEEN?

1286
01:04:56,026 --> 01:04:57,358
YEAH...

1287
01:04:57,394 --> 01:04:59,361
JUST STOPPED BY
TO SAY "SO LONG,"

1288
01:04:59,496 --> 01:05:02,897
AND, UH, GOOD LUCK
IN THE PLAYOFFS, FELLAS.

1289
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:04,832
YOU'RE LEAVING US, HARV?

1290
01:05:04,868 --> 01:05:05,967
YEAH,

1291
01:05:05,969 --> 01:05:07,969
THE CIRCUS IS MOVING ON.

1292
01:05:08,038 --> 01:05:10,772
I'LL SEE ALL YOU BOYS
DOWN THE ROAD.

1293
01:05:11,508 --> 01:05:12,707
[GENTLY]
SEE YA, HARV.

1294
01:05:12,842 --> 01:05:14,442
GOOD LUCK, HARV.

1295
01:05:14,478 --> 01:05:16,177
SEE YA, HARV.

1296
01:05:19,516 --> 01:05:21,049
MR. HARVEY!

1297
01:05:21,051 --> 01:05:23,718
MR. HARVEY...

1298
01:05:23,787 --> 01:05:25,119
I DON'T--

1299
01:05:25,155 --> 01:05:26,788
HOW COULD FOXY JUST FIRE YOU?

1300
01:05:26,790 --> 01:05:28,390
DON'T BE SORE
AT FOXY, KID.

1301
01:05:28,392 --> 01:05:30,725
MAYBE YOU NOTICED I, UH,

1302
01:05:30,860 --> 01:05:34,162
I GOT A LITTLE PROBLEM.

1303
01:05:36,333 --> 01:05:37,798
JEEZ, WELL...

1304
01:05:37,834 --> 01:05:40,334
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO NOW?

1305
01:05:40,370 --> 01:05:43,270
I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE SCOUT A LITTLE?

1306
01:05:43,307 --> 01:05:45,206
LOOK, IT CAN GO
JUST LIKE THAT, KID.

1307
01:05:45,275 --> 01:05:48,876
THAT'S WHY THIS TIME
WITH YOU AND MARK

1308
01:05:48,912 --> 01:05:50,144
IS SO SPECIAL
FOR YOUR DAD.

1309
01:05:50,213 --> 01:05:54,349
HE KNOWS HOW FAST IT CAN GO.

1310
01:05:54,484 --> 01:05:56,017
GIVE ME A SHOUT

1311
01:05:56,019 --> 01:05:58,887
WHEN YOU WIN
THE BEST DEFENCEMAN AWARD, OKAY?

1312
01:06:25,916 --> 01:06:29,117
[GAME PLAYS ON TELEVISION]

1313
01:06:29,119 --> 01:06:30,318
<i>...THE SAINTS
ARE ON THE POWER PLAY</i>

1314
01:06:30,387 --> 01:06:32,053
<i>WITH HUGHES IN THE BOX.</i>

1315
01:06:32,055 --> 01:06:35,557
<i>MIKE WALTON ENTERS
THE FACE-OFF CIRCLE...</i>

1316
01:06:37,227 --> 01:06:39,060
<i>NOW, OFF THE FACE-OFF,
WALTON GETS IT TO SMITH.</i>

1317
01:06:39,195 --> 01:06:41,396
<i>SMITH MOVES IN ACROSS,
GETS IT TO GALLANT.</i>

1318
01:06:41,465 --> 01:06:43,865
<i>GALLANT MOVES OVER--
BACK TO WALTON!</i>

1319
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:46,001
<i>HE SCORES!</i>

1320
01:06:46,136 --> 01:06:49,337
<i>POINT #101 FOR MIKE WALTON,</i>

1321
01:06:49,472 --> 01:06:53,141
<i>WHO PASSES THE INJURED
GORDIE HOWE IN SCORING.</i>

1322
01:06:53,210 --> 01:06:55,410
<i>NOT A GREAT BIRTHDAY PRESENT
FOR MR. HOCKEY,</i>

1323
01:06:55,412 --> 01:06:59,914
<i>WHO TURNED 46 TODAY.</i>

1324
01:07:03,220 --> 01:07:06,321
CATHY HAS
YOUR CAKE READY.

1325
01:07:14,231 --> 01:07:15,563
[SIGHS]

1326
01:07:18,568 --> 01:07:21,503
SO, DO I LIGHT
THE CANDLES OR NOT?

1327
01:07:21,638 --> 01:07:25,340
SURE, ALL 146 OF THEM.

1328
01:07:36,053 --> 01:07:37,185
YOUR DAUGHTER'S WAITING

1329
01:07:37,254 --> 01:07:38,185
TO CELEBRATE
YOUR BIRTHDAY WITH YOU.

1330
01:07:38,221 --> 01:07:39,386
I'M NOT IN THE MOOD.

1331
01:07:39,423 --> 01:07:40,588
OH, COME ON, GORDIE.

1332
01:07:40,723 --> 01:07:42,189
BLOW OUT THE CANDLES.

1333
01:07:42,225 --> 01:07:45,527
WISH FOR A NEW LEG.

1334
01:07:45,662 --> 01:07:49,531
IT WAS IMPORTANT FOR ME
TO WIN IT, COLLEEN.

1335
01:07:49,666 --> 01:07:53,334
TO PROVE ALL
THE NAYSAYERS WRONG.

1336
01:07:57,140 --> 01:07:58,406
YOU KNOW,
I CAME TO HOUSTON

1337
01:07:58,408 --> 01:08:02,009
TO WATCH YOU PLAY HOCKEY
WITH OUR SONS,

1338
01:08:02,079 --> 01:08:04,946
TO TEACH THEM.

1339
01:08:06,550 --> 01:08:09,484
WHAT DO YOU THINK
THIS IS GOING TO TEACH THEM?

1340
01:08:13,557 --> 01:08:18,225
YOU WON YOUR LAST STANLEY CUP
IN 1955.

1341
01:08:18,261 --> 01:08:20,227
[CHUCKLES RUEFULLY]

1342
01:08:20,263 --> 01:08:22,029
WHAT DO YOU THINK
ALL THE NAYSAYERS

1343
01:08:22,099 --> 01:08:24,632
ARE GOING TO THINK?

1344
01:08:24,668 --> 01:08:25,967
THEY PROBABLY THINK

1345
01:08:26,102 --> 01:08:29,204
YOU'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO DO IT AGAIN.

1346
01:08:32,042 --> 01:08:35,376
YOU HAVE WORKED SO HARD.

1347
01:08:37,180 --> 01:08:40,982
NOW YOU HAVE A CHANCE
TO WIN THE CHAMPIONSHIP

1348
01:08:41,051 --> 01:08:43,151
WITH YOUR SONS.

1349
01:08:48,658 --> 01:08:52,660
DO YOU EVER GET TIRED
OF BEING RIGHT?

1350
01:08:52,795 --> 01:08:54,762
[CHUCKLES]

1351
01:08:59,102 --> 01:09:00,268
SO YOU WANT TO EAT THE CAKE,

1352
01:09:00,403 --> 01:09:03,204
OR SHOULD I GIVE IT
TO THE LAST TWO COWS?

1353
01:09:09,379 --> 01:09:11,145
DO YOU THINK DAD
SAW THE GAME TONIGHT?

1354
01:09:11,214 --> 01:09:14,215
OBVIOUSLY.
HE'S GONNA BE PEEVED.

1355
01:09:14,217 --> 01:09:17,351
IT'S MR. NORRIS.
WHAT DO WE DO?

1356
01:09:17,387 --> 01:09:19,620
MR. NORRIS,
HOW YOU DOING?

1357
01:09:19,656 --> 01:09:22,356
BOYS.

1358
01:09:22,425 --> 01:09:27,028
YOU MADE A BIG, BIG MISTAKE,
YOU KNOW THAT?

1359
01:09:27,097 --> 01:09:30,031
YOU'RE NEVER
GOING TO PLAY IN THE NHL NOW.

1360
01:09:30,166 --> 01:09:31,799
YOU CAN THANK YOUR FATHER
FOR THAT.

1361
01:09:33,102 --> 01:09:35,503
WELL, I HOPE
YOU'RE WRONG, MR. NORRIS,

1362
01:09:35,638 --> 01:09:36,570
BUT IT WAS WORTH IT.

1363
01:09:36,606 --> 01:09:37,771
WE GOT TO PLAY

1364
01:09:37,807 --> 01:09:40,708
WITH THE GREATEST
DETROIT RED WING EVER.

1365
01:09:40,744 --> 01:09:42,143
IT WAS NICE SEEING Y'ALL.

1366
01:09:43,813 --> 01:09:45,179
THAT WAS AWKWARD.

1367
01:09:45,182 --> 01:09:46,181
YEAH, I KNOW.

1368
01:09:54,257 --> 01:09:55,723
LATE FLIGHT?

1369
01:09:55,792 --> 01:09:57,191
NO, WE GOT IN ON TIME.

1370
01:09:57,194 --> 01:09:59,460
THE BOYS HAD
A PARTY AT GRIFF'S.

1371
01:09:59,529 --> 01:10:02,497
LAST CHANCE
BEFORE THE PLAYOFFS.

1372
01:10:05,068 --> 01:10:06,267
YOU KNOW, I'VE BEEN
WATCHING YOU SIGN THOSE THINGS

1373
01:10:06,336 --> 01:10:07,668
ALL MY LIFE,

1374
01:10:07,704 --> 01:10:09,604
AND I STILL DON'T GET IT.

1375
01:10:09,673 --> 01:10:11,573
I MEAN, WHY SIGN THEM
AHEAD OF TIME?

1376
01:10:13,076 --> 01:10:14,676
WELL...

1377
01:10:14,678 --> 01:10:17,211
PEOPLE THAT WANT 'EM,

1378
01:10:17,280 --> 01:10:19,747
IF YOU GET 'EM RIGHT
AND READY FOR 'EM,

1379
01:10:19,749 --> 01:10:22,450
IT GIVES YOU MORE TIME
TO TALK TO THEM.

1380
01:10:24,087 --> 01:10:26,754
THAT'S YOU, DAD.

1381
01:10:26,790 --> 01:10:29,757
YOU KNOW, WE RAN INTO MR. NORRIS
AT THE MINNESOTA AIRPORT TODAY.

1382
01:10:29,826 --> 01:10:30,758
YEAH?

1383
01:10:31,694 --> 01:10:34,028
DID HE TALK TO YOU?

1384
01:10:34,097 --> 01:10:36,163
OH, YEAH.

1385
01:10:36,233 --> 01:10:38,499
HE SAID WE'D NEVER PLAY
IN THE NHL.

1386
01:10:42,572 --> 01:10:45,640
YOU DON'T LISTEN
TO THAT CRAP, SON. OKAY?

1387
01:10:47,310 --> 01:10:48,576
MARTY SAID IT WAS WORTH IT

1388
01:10:48,645 --> 01:10:51,212
'CAUSE WE GOT TO PLAY
WITH OUR OLD MAN.

1389
01:10:53,717 --> 01:10:55,316
MARTY SAID THAT?

1390
01:10:55,451 --> 01:10:56,717
YEAH.

1391
01:10:56,786 --> 01:10:58,119
I LET HIM SAY IT,

1392
01:10:58,254 --> 01:11:01,122
'CAUSE, UH,
HE'S OLDER THAN ME, BUT...

1393
01:11:01,191 --> 01:11:02,390
YEAH.

1394
01:11:12,669 --> 01:11:13,534
[PATS SHOULDER]

1395
01:11:13,603 --> 01:11:14,402
NIGHT, OLD MAN.

1396
01:11:14,537 --> 01:11:16,604
NIGHT, YOUNG MAN.

1397
01:11:29,686 --> 01:11:33,621
[♪♪]

1398
01:11:45,502 --> 01:11:46,434
[ROAR OF CROWD]

1399
01:11:46,569 --> 01:11:49,370
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

1400
01:11:49,406 --> 01:11:50,504
[ANNOUNCER]:<i> IT'S A SWEEP!</i>

1401
01:11:50,573 --> 01:11:51,572
<i>THE HOUSTON AEROS
DEFEAT THE JETS</i>

1402
01:11:51,641 --> 01:11:53,107
<i>IN FOUR STRAIGHT,</i>

1403
01:11:53,242 --> 01:11:55,176
<i>SO NOW THEY'LL MOVE ON
TO MINNESOTA,</i>

1404
01:11:55,245 --> 01:11:59,313
<i>IN WHAT'S EXPECTED TO BE
A MUCH ROUGHER PLAY-OFF SERIES,</i>

1405
01:11:59,382 --> 01:12:02,249
<i>BECAUSE THEY ARE
THE FIGHTING SAINTS.</i>

1406
01:12:02,319 --> 01:12:03,851
- ELBOWS.
- BOBBY.

1407
01:12:03,920 --> 01:12:05,253
TELL YOU WHAT,

1408
01:12:05,388 --> 01:12:07,188
NEXT YEAR, WE'LL CALL IT
"OUR LEAGUE," HUH?

1409
01:12:07,190 --> 01:12:08,323
WELL, THANK YOU.

1410
01:12:08,458 --> 01:12:11,459
YOU'LL GET US NEXT YEAR,
IF I RETIRE AGAIN.

1411
01:12:11,461 --> 01:12:12,459
[CHUCKLING]

1412
01:12:12,495 --> 01:12:13,527
GOOD WORK...

1413
01:12:13,563 --> 01:12:16,264
LOOKS LIKE YOU GOT
THE HALL TONIGHT, STANNY.

1414
01:12:16,266 --> 01:12:18,599
WINNIPEG'S BEEN
LUCKY FOR ME.

1415
01:12:18,735 --> 01:12:20,534
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1416
01:12:20,603 --> 01:12:21,802
WELL, GO ON,

1417
01:12:21,838 --> 01:12:23,638
LET THE GAL IN
ON YOUR WAY OUT.

1418
01:12:28,878 --> 01:12:30,210
HEY, MRS. HOWE.

1419
01:12:30,246 --> 01:12:31,345
GREAT GAME, JACK.

1420
01:12:31,348 --> 01:12:32,580
SORRY TO KICK YOU OUT.

1421
01:12:36,753 --> 01:12:37,885
IT'S NUMBER 4. WALTON.

1422
01:12:37,887 --> 01:12:38,686
MIKE!

1423
01:12:38,755 --> 01:12:41,155
MIKE, FOR TELEVISION,

1424
01:12:41,290 --> 01:12:42,489
IS IT GONNA BE
A ROUGH ONE, MIKE?

1425
01:12:42,525 --> 01:12:43,558
WE CAN PLAY IT
ANY WAY THEY LIKE.

1426
01:12:43,693 --> 01:12:46,294
ANY SPECIAL PLANS
FOR THE HOWE LINE?

1427
01:12:46,296 --> 01:12:47,694
STOP 'EM.

1428
01:12:47,731 --> 01:12:50,230
WE KNOW GORDIE'S ON A MISSION,
BUT, HEY, SO ARE WE.

1429
01:12:50,266 --> 01:12:53,434
HOWE'S GONNA WISH
HE STAYED RETIRED.

1430
01:12:53,470 --> 01:12:54,602
[CACKLES]

1431
01:12:56,706 --> 01:12:57,772
WHO'S THAT?

1432
